Name: Cold Feet
Description: Places Death Rime Stacks on an enemy that can be dispelled by moving away from the initial cast point.  If the enemy unit doesn't move outside of the given range, it will be stunned and frozen in place after 4 seconds.

Name: Ice Vortex
Description: Creates a vortex of icy energy that applies Death Rime Stacks and increases magic damage done to enemies in its range.

Name: Chilling Touch
Description: Enhances Ancient Apparition's attack with increased range and heavy magic damage. Applies a Death Rime Stack that lasts for %duration% seconds. Additionally applies a %slow%% slow for %slow_duration% seconds.

Name: Ice Blast
Description: Launches a tracer toward any location on the battlefield, which must be triggered again to mark the area to be blasted by a damaging explosion of hail. The further the tracer travels, the larger the explosion will be. Enemies caught in the explosion, or who touch the icy ball of hail as it travels, are Frostbitten, gaining Death Rime Stacks and prevented from regenerating or healing. If a Frostbitten unit's health drops below a certain percentage, they will instantly shatter.

Name: Death Rime
Description: Ancient Apparition's abilities apply Death Rime Stacks on enemies. Death Rime slows enemies' movement speed and deals damage over time.

Name: Release
Description: Releases the ice blast to explode at the tracer's current location.

Name: Ice Age
Description: Causes all enemy heroes in a %radius% radius to take %damage% damage per second and -%health_degen%% Health/Lifesteal Regeneration for %duration% seconds.

Name: Mana Break
Description: Burns an opponent's mana on each attack and deals damage equal to a percentage of the mana burnt.

Name: Persecutor
Description: Attacks slow enemies based on how much mana they are missing. Min slow at %mana_threshold%% mana, up to max slow at %zero_tooltip%% mana. No effect if enemy is above %mana_threshold%% mana.

Name: Blink
Description: Short distance teleportation that allows Anti-Mage to move in and out of combat.

Name: Spell Shield
Description: Increases Anti-Mage's resistance to magic damage.

Name: Counterspell
Description: Passively grants magic resistance. Counterspell may be activated to create an anti-magic shell around Anti-Mage that blocks any targeted spells.
AbilityDraftNote: Shard: Access Counterspell Ally by toggling auto-cast on Counterspell.

Name: Counterspell Ally
Description: Counterspell Ally may be activated to create an anti-magic shell around an allied hero that blocks any targeted spells. Any time a spell is blocked by Counterspell or Counterspell Ally, an illusion of Anti-Mage will be created next to the enemy.

Name: Mana Void
Description: For each point of mana missing by the target unit, damage is dealt to it and surrounding enemies.  The main target is also mini-stunned.

Name: Blink Fragment
Description: Blinks an illusion to the target enemy or location, which attacks for a brief time. Counterspell is replicated on the Blink Fragment illusion.

Name: Berserker's Call
Description: Axe taunts nearby enemy units, forcing them to attack him while he gains bonus armor during the duration.
AbilityDraftNote: Must draft Battle Hunger for Scepter upgrade to work.

Name: Battle Hunger
Description: Enrages an enemy unit, causing it to take damage over time until it kills another unit or the duration ends. The damage is increased by a factor of Axe's armor. The enemy is also slowed as long as they are facing away from Axe.

Name: Counter Helix
Description: After a set number of attacks, Axe will perform a helix counter attack, dealing pure damage to all nearby enemies.

Name: Culling Blade
Description: Axe spots a weakness and strikes, dealing pure damage. When an enemy hero is killed with Culling Blade, its cooldown is reset, and all nearby allied units gain bonus movement speed and armor.

Name: One Man Army
Description: Axe gains Strength based on his armor as long as he's away from his allies.

Name: Coat of Blood
Description: Whenever Axe gets a kill, he permanently gains %armor_per_kill% armor. Killing with Culling Blade gives %culling_blade_multiplier%x that amount.

Name: +{s:bonus_speed_bonus}% Movement Speed per active Battle Hunger
Enfeeble
Description: Deals damage every second and lowers the enemy's total attack damage and cast range.

Name: Brain Sap
Description: Feasts on the vital energies of an enemy unit, healing Bane and dealing damage.

Name: Fiend's Grip
Description: CHANNELED - Grips an enemy unit, disabling it and causing heavy damage over time, while stealing mana every %fiend_grip_tick_interval% seconds based on the unit's maximum mana.

Name: Nightmare
Description: Puts the target enemy or friendly Hero to sleep. Sleeping units are awakened when damaged. If the target was directly attacked, the Nightmare passes to the attacking unit. Bane can attack and damage Nightmared targets freely.
AbilityDraftNote: Hero that drafts Nightmare can continue to attack Nightmared units. Bane can also attack even if he didn't draft this ability.

Name: Nightmare End
Description: Ends all ongoing Nightmares.

Name: Ichor of Nyctasha
Description: Bane's attribute gains are always evenly distributed across all three attributes (items that grant +3 Strength will now grant +1 Str/Agi/Int).

Name: Wild Axes
Description: Beastmaster sends his axes flying and calls them home again, slicing through enemy units and trees along their path.  Each axe can hit an enemy once, and amplifies subsequent damage from Beastmaster and his units.

Name: Call of the Wild Boar
Description: Beastmaster calls forth a Boar to aid in the battlefield. The Boar has a passive poison attack that slows attack and movement speeds.

Name: Dive Bomb
Description: Flies towards the target enemy, dealing damage and rooting it.

Name: Call of the Wild Hawk
Description: Beastmaster summons a hawk that circles around Beastmaster and dive-bombs at enemies with a base attack rate of every %hawk_base_attack_interval%s, damaging and rooting them. Attack rate increases with the Hawk's attack speed. Prioritizes heroes.
AbilityDraftNote: Also grants Call of the Wild Boar. Accessible by toggling auto-cast.

Name: Hawk Attack
Description: Order all hawks to dive bomb the selected target

Name: Invisibility
Description: If motionless for some time, the hawk becomes invisible.

Name: Poison
Description: Inflicts a poison that slows attack and movement speeds.

Name: Poison
Description: Inflicts a poison that slows attack and movement speeds.

Name: Inner Beast
Description: Untaps the inner fury of Beastmaster and units he controls, passively increasing their attack speed.

Name: Primal Roar
Description: Beastmaster lets loose a deafening roar that stuns, and shoves open a path to its target. All units in the path of the roar are damaged, while units shoved aside by the roar have their movement and attack speed slowed. Additionally, Beastmaster and his units gain %movement_speed%% movement speed for 3 seconds.

Name: Drums of Slom
Description:
Attacks from Beastmaster or a nearby unit he controls will cause him bang his drum, dealing damage to nearby units and healing Beastmaster and units under his control for a portion of the damage dealt. Every attack decreases the interval between drum hits down to a minimum of %min_drum_hit_interval%s between hits after %max_stacks% attacks. If no attacks are made, the intervals gradually increase.

Using Primal Roar counts as 10/15/20 attacks, based on the current level of Primal Roar.

Name: Rugged
Description: Beastmaster's melee hero Damage Block Chance is increased from %damage_block_pct_fifty_tooltip%% to %damage_block_pct_vs_creeps%% versus non-hero units.

Name: +{s:bonus_boar_bonus_damage} Damage to Beastmaster and his units
+{s:bonus_ms} Movespeed Aura to Beastmaster and his units
Description: The Movespeed Aura is global, persists through death, and affects Beastmaster and all units under his control.

Name: +{s:bonus_hp} Max Health Aura to Beastmaster and his units
Description: The Max Health Aura is global, persists through death, and affects Beastmaster and all units under his control.

Name: +{s:bonus_damage_amp}% Wild Axes Damage Amp Per Stack
No Wild Axes Cooldown
Description: Axes still must return to Beastmaster before they can be cast again.

Name: Bloodrage
Description: Drives Bloodseeker into a bloodthirsty rage which causes him to attack faster and deal more spell damage at the cost of a percentage of his health per second. Provides half attack speed to allied heroes.

Name: Blood Rite
Description: Bloodseeker baptizes an area in sacred blood. After %delay_plus_castpoint_tooltip% seconds the ritual completes, causing any enemies caught in the area to take damage and become silenced.

Name: Thirst
Description: Bloodseeker is invigorated by the wounds of his enemies, gaining bonus movement speed when an enemy hero's health falls below %min_bonus_pct%%, with the bonuses increasing as their health falls further. If an enemy hero's health falls below %invis_threshold_pct%%, he will also gain vision and True Sight of that hero. Bonuses stack per hero. Unlocks max movement speed for Bloodseeker.

Name: Rupture
Description: Causes an enemy unit's skin to rupture, dealing initial damage based on its current health. If the unit moves, it takes damage based on the distance moved.

Name: Blood Mist
Description:
Bloodseeker sprays his blood continuously in the area around him, losing health to damage and slow his enemies. While active, Sanguivore's healing is increased. Cannot be turned off while on cooldown.

Additionally, passively turns all your overheal from your own abilities into an all damage barrier up to 50% of Bloodseeker's Max Health. Barrier amount decays by %barrier_decay_pct%% per second.

Name: Sanguivore
Description:
Bloodseeker restores some life when he kills a unit, equal to %heal_hp_pct_per_level%% of the units max health per Bloodseeker's Level plus a base of %base_heal%.

Restores for half values if an ally kills a nearby enemy hero.

Name: Penitence
Description: Forces an enemy unit to move slower and for allies to attack it more quickly. Chen can attack the Penitence target with bonus attack range.

Name: Test of Faith
Description: Deals random damage to test an enemy unit's faith. Heals a random amount to allied units. Always applies the maximum effect when cast on yourself.

Name: Divine Favor
Description:
Passively provides an aura that grants increased health regeneration. Can be cast on allies to provide them with bonus armor and increasing the healing and health regeneration they receive.

If cast on Chen, all units controlled by Chen will be teleported to him. Taking damage from enemy heroes or their units will cancel the teleport.

Teleports an allied unit back to the base.  Creeps are teleported instantly, while Heroes have a delay before teleporting. If cast on Chen, all units controlled by Chen through Holy Persuasion will be teleported to him after a delay.

Name: Holy Persuasion
Description: Chen takes control of an enemy or neutral creep and receives a percentage of its bounty. Its maximum health is set to %health_min% + %bonus_health_per_level% per Chen Level. Converted creeps will have increased movement speed and bonus damage.
AbilityDraftNote: Max number of Ancient creeps controllable equal to level of ultimate.

Name: Martyrdom
Description: Sacrifice the life of this unit to heal an ally or damage an enemy with the current level of Hand of God.

Name: Hand of God
Description: Heals all allied heroes on the map as well as all units under Chen's control. A large heal is applied at first and a slow heal over time is applied for %hot_duration% seconds afterwards.

Name: Summon Convert
Description:
Chen summons a convert to fight for him. The convert gains bonuses from Holy Persuasion and dies if Chen dies. Its maximum health is set to %health_min% + %bonus_health_per_level% per Chen Level.

The spell stays on cooldown while the convert is alive, but refreshes whenever Chen respawns. The Convert counts towards Holy Persuasion max unit count.

Name: +{s:bonus_heal_amount}/+{s:bonus_heal_per_second} Hand of God Heal/Heal Over Time
Hand of God applies a Strong Dispel
Let It Go
Description: Creates an icy path towards the targeted direction, allowing you to move faster and path freely. Enemies walking over this path will move slower.

Name: Crystal Nova
Description: A burst of damaging frost slows enemy movement in the targeted area.

Name: Frostbite
Description: Encases an enemy unit in ice, prohibiting movement and attack, while dealing damage over time. Deals %creep_multiplier%x damage to non-ancient creeps.
AbilityDraftNote: Shard: Access Crystal Clone by toggling auto-cast on Frostbite.

Name: Arcane Aura
Description: Gives additional mana regeneration to all friendly units on the map. Allies within a %proximity_bonus_radius% radius of Crystal Maiden receive %proximity_bonus_factor%x the mana regeneration.

Name: Freezing Field
Description: CHANNELED - Surrounds Crystal Maiden with 100 random icy explosions that slow enemies and deal massive damage. Lasts %abilitychanneltime% seconds.
AbilityDraftNote: Frostbite must be drafted for Aghanim's Scepter upgrade to work.

Name: Stop Freezing Field
Description: Immediately stops the Freezing Field

Name: Crystal Clone
Description: Slides in a direction, creating a crystal clone of herself in her place and disjointing incoming projectiles. If the clone takes enough damage or times out, it shatters, Frostbiting enemies in a %frostbite_radius% AoE around its place. The Clone can also be destroyed by Crystal Maiden's own spells.

Name: Blueheart Floe
Description: Crystal Maiden has %mana_regen_multiplier%% Mana Regeneration Amplification.

Name: Normal Punch
Description: Passive ability. Causes Dark Seer's next attack on a hero to have True Strike, knock a replica out of the victim, damaging and stunning them based on how far Dark Seer has moved in the past %recent_duration% seconds. Max power is reached after %max_distance% distance moved.

Name: Vacuum
Description: Dark Seer creates a vacuum over the target area that sucks in enemy units, disrupting them and dealing damage.

Name: Ion Shell
Description: Surrounds the target unit with a bristling shield that damages enemy units in an area around it.

Name: Surge
Description: Charges a target friendly unit with power, giving it a brief burst of phased movement speed. Allows the unit to reach maximum movement speed and cannot be slowed.

Name: Wall of Replica
Description: Raises a wall of warping light that slows, damages, and creates replicas of any enemy hero who crosses it. Enemy replicas serve at the Dark Seer's will. Replicas last until they are destroyed, or until the wall's duration ends.

Name: Quick Wit
Description: Dark Seer also gains Attack Speed from Intelligence.

Name: Heart of Battle
Description: Dark Seer moves faster when near other heroes.

Name: Mental Fortitude
Description: Dark Seer's Intelligence cannot be lower than the average of his Strength and Agility.

Name: Poison Touch
Description: Releases a cone of poison that strikes multiple enemy units. Deals damage over time and slows the targets. Anytime the targets get attacked by Dazzle, the debuff duration is refreshed and slow is increased.

Name: Shallow Grave
Description: An ally blessed with Shallow Grave, no matter how close to death, cannot die while under its protection. Healing on that ally is also amplified for the duration based on the hero's HP.

Name: Shadow Wave
Description: Sends out a bolt of power that arcs between allies, healing them while damaging any enemy units standing nearby.  Dazzle is always healed by Shadow Wave.

Name: Weave
Description: Applies a buff that increases the armor of allied heroes while decreasing the armor of enemy heroes in the target area over time.

Name: Bad Juju
Description: Decreases the remaining cooldown of all other abilities. Casting Bad Juju temporarily increases its health cost.

Name: Good Juju
Description: Whenever Dazzle Casts a Spell, all other abilities currently on cooldown have their cooldowns reduced.

Name: Weave
Description: Dazzle's abilities apply Weave to both allies and enemies they affect, increasing allied armor and reducing enemy armor. Multiple instances of this effect stack.

Name: Nothl Boon
Description: Dazzle's overhealing is converted into a barrier.

Name: +{s:bonus_attack_range_bonus} Poison Touch Attack Range
Description: +{s:bonus_attack_range_bonus} Attack Range when attacking an enemy affected by Poison Touch

Name: Fireball
Description: Ignites an area, dealing damage over time that lingers on enemies in it. Has reduced cast range when melee.

Name: Breathe Fire
Description: Unleashes a breath of fire in front of Dragon Knight that burns enemies and reduces the damage their attacks deal.

Name: Dragon Tail
Description: Dragon Knight smites an enemy unit in melee range with his shield, stunning it and dealing damage.  When in Elder Dragon Form, the cast range increases to %dragon_cast_range%.

Name: Wyrm's Wrath
Description: The life blood of the Dragon improves Dragon Knight's attacks. When in Dragon form, these attack effects are stronger.

Name: Dragon Blood
Description: The life blood of the Dragon improves Dragon Knight's health regeneration and armor. Amount for both values is increased by %level_mult% per level and is multiplied when in Dragon Form.

Name: Elder Dragon Form
Description: Dragon Knight takes the form of one of three powerful elder dragons. Increases movement speed and attack damage, with Wyrm's Wrath on-hit effects applying to all enemies near the target. Increases Dragon Tail range. Increases health regeneration and armor bonuses from Dragon Blood.
AbilityDraftNote: Shard: Grants Fireball.

Name: +{s:bonus_dragon_aoe} AoE Dragon Tail During Elder Dragon Form
+{s:bonus_dragon_form_bonus_pct}% Breathe Fire Damage/Cast Range in Dragon Form
Devour
Description: Consumes an enemy or neutral creep, acquiring any special abilities that it possessed. If alt-cast is deactivated, Doom will not acquire the creep's abilities. Duration is equal to the cooldown.
AbilityDraftNote: Devour will only acquire the passive abilities that the creep possessed. If Rearm is drafted and cast, this ability's cooldown will not be reset.

Name: Lvl ? Pain
Description: Doom's attacks deal %bonus_damage%% bonus damage to heroes whose level is lower than Doom's level.

Name: Scorched Earth
Description: Carpets the nearby earth in flames which damage enemies, while also granting him increased movement speed.

Name: Infernal Blade
Description: Doom swings his burning sword, igniting the enemy. Stuns for %ministun_duration% seconds and applies a %burn_duration% second burn that deals a base damage plus a percentage of the target's Max HP as damage per second.

Name: Doom
Description:
Inflicts a curse that dispels an enemy Hero and prevents them from casting spells or healing in any way, while taking damage over time.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Devoured Ability
Description: This slot will be replaced with abilities acquired using Devour.

Name: Devoured Ability
Description: This slot will be replaced with abilities acquired using Devour.

Name: Devil's Bargain
Description: Doom can sell items for %bonus_item_sellback_percent%% of their value, but his buyback costs are increased by %bonus_buyback_penalty%%.

Name: +{s:bonus_burn_damage_pct}% Infernal Blade Max HP As Damage
Frost Arrows
Description: Adds a freezing effect to Drow's attacks, slowing enemy movement and dealing bonus damage.  Slow lasts %abilityduration% seconds.

Name: Multishot
Description: CHANNELED - Drow releases a flurry of arrows in continuous salvos, hitting enemies for extra damage and applying Frost Arrows. Lasts up to %abilitychanneltime% seconds.

Name: Silence
Description: Stops all enemy units in a target area from casting spells.

Name: Gust
Description: Releases a wave that silences and knocks back and reveals invisible enemy units. Knockback distance is relative to how close they are to Drow.

Name: Precision Aura
Description: Grants Drow and nearby ranged heroes with bonus agility based on Drow's current agility and level.

Name: Marksmanship
Description: Drow's experiences in battle grant her a chance to launch arrows with incredible accuracy and effectiveness. Pierces through the enemy's defenses, ignoring their base armor. This ability is disabled if there is an enemy hero within %disable_range% range.

Name: Glacier
Description: Drow creates a hill of ice beneath her. While standing on the hill, attackers gain bonus attack range and high ground advantage - they cannot miss and gain flying vision. Drow additionally gets bonus Multishot arrows per wave while on the hill. The front of the hill obscures vision and cannot be moved through except by Drow. Does not interrupt Multishot when cast.

Name: Creep Rally
Description: Precision Aura also grants 3% Attack Speed per level to nearby ranged non-hero units.

Name: Vantage Point
Description: Drow deals %damage_bonus%% more damage when attacking from high ground.

Name: Fissure
Description: Slams the ground with a mighty totem, creating an impassable ridge of stone while stunning and damaging enemy units along its line.
AbilityDraftNote: Requires drafting Aftershock for Shard upgrade to work.

Name: Enchant Totem
Description: Empowers Earthshaker's totem, causing it to deal extra damage and have %bonus_attack_range% bonus attack range on the next attack.

Name: Aftershock
Description: Causes the earth to shake underfoot, adding additional damage and stuns to nearby enemy units when Earthshaker casts his abilities.

Name: Echo Slam
Description: Shockwaves travel through the ground, damaging enemy units.  Each enemy hit causes an echo to damage nearby units. Real heroes cause two echoes.

Name: Spirit Cairn
Description: When Earthshaker dies, a %fissure_radius% radius fissure is created where he died. This fissure blocks movement and allows Earthshaker to continue to gain experience around it. It remains until Earthshaker respawns.

Name: Slugger
Description: Enemies killed with Enchant Totem or Earthshaker's other abilities are sent flying, dealing damage to enemies they hit.

Name: Untouchable
Description: Enchantress beguiles her enemies, slowing their attacks when she is attacked.

Name: Sproink
Description: Leaps backward, dodges incoming projectiles, and launches an Impetus attack on the %attack_targets% furthest enemy units within Enchantress' attack range + %bonus_attack_range%.

Name: Little Friends
Description: Enchantress roots an enemy unit. All creeps, ally, enemy and neutral within a radius will gain bonus movement and attack speed and attack the chosen target for %duration% seconds.

Name: Enchant
Description:
Enchantress charms an enemy. If the enemy is a hero, they are dispelled and slowed for %slow_duration%s.

 If the enemy is a creep, she brings it under her control and receives %xp_gain_pct%% of their experience bounty.  Enchantress can control creeps for up to %dominate_duration%s. 

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Nature's Attendants
Description: A cloud of wisps heals Enchantress and any friendly units nearby.

Name: Impetus
Description: Places an enchantment on each attack while activated, causing it to deal additional damage based on how far away the target is.  The farther the target, the greater the damage dealt. Deals double damage to creeps and illusions.

Name: Rabble-Rouser
Description: All neutral camps deal more damage to enemy heroes. Damage increase is %base_damage_amp%% + %damage_amp_per_level%% per Enchantress's hero level.

Name: +{s:bonus_bonus_health} Health / +{s:bonus_bonus_damage} Damage  for Enchantress and her units
+{s:bonus_bonus_attackspeed} Attack Speed for Enchantress and her units
Malefice
Description: Focuses Enigma's power on a target, causing it to take damage and become repeatedly stunned for multiple instances.  An instance strikes every %tick_rate% seconds.

Name: Demonic Summoning
Description: Summons three fragments of Enigma himself at the cost of health.  The eidolons health is increased by %current_health_pct%% of Enigma's current health. These eidolons are all under Enigma's control, and repeated successful attacks cause them to multiply.  When this happens, the eidolons have their health restored.

Name: Midnight Pulse
Description: Steeps an area in dark resonance, dealing %base_damage% + a percentage of the enemies current HP as damage.

Name: Black Hole
Description: CHANNELED - Summons a vortex that sucks in nearby enemy units.  Enemies affected by Black Hole cannot move, attack, or cast spells.

Name: Gravity Well
Description: Allies within %max_dist% distance from Enigma have up to %damage_reduction%% Damage Reduction. Effect starts at 0% at max distance and increases to its maximum strength when the ally is at %min_dist% distance. Does not affect Enigma itself.

Name: Splitting Image
Description: Enigma spawns Eidolons upon receiving damage.

Name: Event Horizon
Description: Units in a %radius% radius moving away from Enigma have a %speed_bonus%% movespeed penalty.

Name: Time Walk
Description: Rushes to a target location while backtracking any damage taken the last %backtrack_duration% seconds.

Name: Distortion Field
Description: Enemy Attack Projectiles within %slow_distance_max% radius are slowed by %attack_projectile_slow%%.

Name: Backtrack
Description: Faceless Void has %backtrack_per_level%% chance per level to dodge each instance of damage he receives.

Name: Reverse Time Walk
Description: Available for 1.5 seconds after landing Time Walk. If used in this period, you will reverse your time walk back to your previous cast location. Does not affect health or proc scepter hits.

Name: Time Lock
Description: Adds the chance for an attack to lock an enemy unit in time while attacking it a second time.
AbilityDraftNote: In Ability Draft, does stack with Skull Basher.

Name: Time Dilation
Description: Faceless Void traps all nearby enemies in a time dilation field for %duration% seconds, extending their cooldowns and slowing their movement and attack speed by %slow%% for each cooldown extended. Deals bonus damage per second for each cooldown. The debuff does not tick down while inside Chronosphere.

Name: Chronosphere
Description: Creates a blister in spacetime, trapping all units caught in its sphere of influence and causes you to move very quickly inside it.  All ability and item cooldowns are frozen. Only Faceless Void and any units he controls are unaffected. Invisible enemies in the sphere will be revealed.
AbilityDraftNote: Faceless Void can move freely within the Chronosphere without drafting Chronosphere and regardless of team.

Name: Time Zone
Description:
Creates a blister in spacetime, altering the movement, attack, cast, projectile, and turn rate speed of all units inside. Allies have increased speed and enemies have decreased speed.

Enemies are leashed inside the Time Zone.

Name: +{s:dodge_chance_pct}% Backtrack Chance
Description: Grants a {s:dodge_chance_pct}% chance to avoid damage entirely. Disabled by break.

Name: Sprout
Description: Sprouts a ring of trees around a unit, damaging and trapping it in place and providing vision in a %vision_range% radius.

Name: Greater Sprout
Description: Creates a larger circle of trees in a 300 AoE for %duration% seconds. Ensnares enemies inside for 2 seconds, dealing 150 damage per second.

Name: Teleportation
Description: Teleports to any point on the map. Gains a barrier after arriving to its destination.

Name: Nature's Call
Description: Converts an area of trees into Treants under the command of Nature's Prophet.

Name: Wrath of Nature
Description: Damaging energy bounces around the map, striking enemies that are in vision starting with those closest to the cast point. Each enemy hit beyond the first adds damage, up to the maximum after %max_targets% are hit.

Name: Curse of the Oldgrowth
Description: Applies a curse on all enemy heroes within %range% range, displaying them in fog, slowing them, and causing damage over time based on the number of trees within %radius% radius. Treants count as trees for this purpose.

Name: Hedgerow
Description: Creates a row of hedges in front of Nature's Prophet that blocks incoming enemy attack projectiles. Slows and damages enemies that are too close to the Hedgerow.

Name: Arboreal Might
Description: Nature's Prophet gains a stack of bonus attack damage for every %trees_per_stack% trees around him. Every attack reduces the stacks of attack damage, but increases Nature's Prophet's armor.

Name: Spirit of the Forest
Description: Nature's Prophet gains %damage_per_tree_pct%% bonus damage for each tree within %radius% and a multiplier of that same bonus for each treant within %radius_treant% distance of him.

Name: {s:bonus_treant_health}x Treant HP/Damage
Description: Also affects Spirit of the Forest

Name: Blade Dance
Description: Gives Juggernaut a chance to deal critical damage on each attack.

Name: Blade Fury
Description: Causes a bladestorm of destructive force around Juggernaut, rendering him debuff immune, increasing his magic resistance by 80%, and dealing damage to nearby enemy units. Juggernaut deals damage in an interval equal to %blade_fury_aspd_multiplier%x his attack speed. Applies a strong dispel at the end of the spin.

Name: Healing Ward
Description: Summons a Healing Ward which heals all nearby allied units, based on their max health.  The Healing Ward moves at %healing_ward_movespeed_tooltip% movement speed after being summoned.  Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.

Name: Omnislash
Description:
Juggernaut leaps towards the target enemy units, and then slashes the target and other nearby enemy units at an increased attack rate. Juggernaut is invulnerable for the duration.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Swiftslash
Description: Performs a short Omnislash for %duration% seconds.

Name: Duelist
Description: Juggernaut deals %front_damage_increase%% more damage to targets that are facing him. Damage bonus always applies during Omnislash.

Name: Bladeform
Description: Juggernaut gains Agility and Movement Speed as long as he's not taking damage.

Name: Tidal Wave
Description: Releases a Tidal Wave that spawns behind Kunkka. Deals damage and drags enemies along it for the duration. Enemies cannot attack while being dragged.

Name: Torrent
Description: Summons a rising torrent that, after a short delay, hurls enemy units into the sky, stunning, dealing damage and slowing movement speed.
AbilityDraftNote: Scepter: Access Torrent Storm by toggling auto-cast on Torrent.

Name: Torrent Storm
Description: Releases a visible Torrent in a random area within %torrent_max_distance% range of the target position once every %torrent_interval% for %torrent_duration% seconds.

Name: Tidebringer
Description: Kunkka's legendary sword grants increased damage and cleaves a large area of effect in front of him for a single strike.

Name: X Marks the Spot
Description: Targets a friendly or enemy Hero, marks their position with an X, and returns them to it after several seconds.  Kunkka can trigger the return at any time during the duration. Lasts twice as long on allied heroes.

Name: Return
Description: Returns the marked hero to the X.

Name: Ghostship
Description: Summons a ghostly ship that sails through the battle before smashing apart, damaging and stunning all enemies caught near the wreckage. Allied heroes touched by the Ghostship are given a strong swig of The Admiral's Rum, receiving bonus movement speed and a delayed reaction to incoming damage.

Name: Admiral's Rum
Description: Damage from enemy heroes, buildings, or Roshan that would reduce Kunkka below a threshold causes him to douse himself with The Admiral's Rum, receiving bonus movement speed and a delayed reaction to incoming damage.

Name: Ghostship Fleet
Description: Spawns 3 Ghostships, {s:value} seconds apart, towards the target location.

Name: +{s:bonus_ally_ms}% X Marks the Spot Move Speed
Description: Affects Allies positively and Enemies negatively

Name: Split Earth
Description: Splits the earth under enemies. Deals damage and stuns for a short duration.

Name: Diabolic Edict
Description: Saturates the area around Leshrac with magical explosions that deal pure damage to enemy units and buildings.  The fewer units available to attack, the more damage those units will take.

Name: Lightning Storm
Description: Summons a lightning storm that blasts the target enemy unit, then strikes any nearby enemy units. Struck enemies have their move speed and attack speed slowed.

Name: Nihilism
Description: Causes Leshrac and all nearby enemies to turn ethereal, preventing them from attacking, slowing them, and making them take more magic damage. Increases Leshrac's speed rather than reducing it. Does not cause Leshrac to take amplified damage.

Name: Pulse Nova
Description: Creates waves of damaging energy around Leshrac, one per second, to damage nearby enemy units. Drains Leshrac's mana with each pulse.

Name: Chronoptic Nourishment
Description: Leshrac restores mana equal to %mana_pct_per_hit%% of damage dealt by his attacks. Only grants mana when attacking enemies that have mana. %creep_penalty_reduction_pct%% mana restoration penalty when attacking creeps.

Name: Defilement
Description: Leshrac gains AoE per intelligence.

Name: Pulse Nova triggers Lightning Storm
Description: Lightning Storm hits a random enemy in Pulse Nova radius every {s:bonus_pulse_nova_lightning_interval}s with a single bolt. Prioritizes heroes.

Name: Frost Blast
Description: Blasts the target enemy unit with damaging frost, dealing area damage and slowing movement and attack rates for %abilityduration% seconds.  The primary target receives both base and area damage.

Name: Unholy Pact
Description: Grants you bonus attack speed for a limited number of attacks, draining a percentage of mana for each hit. Costs a percentage of current health to cast. Lasts up to %duration% seconds or when the attack count is consumed.

Name: Death Charge
Description: Lich cannot gain passive mana regeneration, but any unit dying within %radius% range of Lich restores %mana_restore_pct_from_creep%% of his Max Mana (Dying heroes restore %mana_restore_pct_from_hero%% of Lich's Max Mana). Instant mana restoration from items and abilities apply to Lich as normal.

Name: Sinister Gaze
Description:
CHANNELED. Hypnotizes an enemy unit, causing it to move towards a point between the two of you and drains a percentage of its current mana.

Lich can use his other abilities while channeling this ability.

If cast on a creep lasts %creep_duration_multiplier%x longer and deals %creep_damage% damage per second.

Name: Frost Aura
Description: Allied Aura. Causes all nearby ally attacks to slow enemy movement speed.

Name: Ice Armor
Description: Creates a shield around the target friendly unit or building, which adds armor and slows attacking units. Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.

Name: Frost Shield
Description: Applies a magical frost shield around the target, reducing damage from attacks against it. While the shield is active, ice magic will affect nearby enemy units every %interval% seconds, dealing minor damage and slowing them.

Name: Chain Frost
Description: Releases an orb of frost that bounces between nearby enemy units up to %jumps% times, slowing and damaging each time it hits. Each bounce increases the damage for the subsequent bounces.

Name: Ice Spire
Description:
Creates an Ice Spire at the target spot, slowing enemies around it. Can take 5 hero hits or 10 creep hits and when destroyed it will create a Frost Blast around it.

Chain Frost can be cast on the Spire and can bounce to the Spire if there are no other enemies in range.

Lich can cast Frost Shield on the Spire. Each Frost Shield tick will heal the spire by 1 hero attack.

Name: Rage
Description:
Launch into a maddened rage, becoming Debuff Immune and increasing magic resistance.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Unfettered
Description:
Descend into a violent fury, gaining increased status and magic resistance. Applies a dispel and can be cast while disabled.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel

Name: Feast
Description: Lifestealer's attacks deal damage and provide heal for a percentage of his target's max health. Allows Lifestealer to attack allied creeps at %creep_deny_percent%% health. Lifestealer gains permanent max HP whenever he kills a creep or hero.

Name: Open Wounds
Description: Lifestealer rends an enemy unit, slowing the victim's movement speed and allowing all allies to regain health for a percentage of the damage they deal to that unit. All damage dealt will steal life, including damage from spells. The victim recovers movement speed over the duration.

Name: Ghoul Frenzy
Description: Passively grants Lifestealer Movement and Attack Speed.

Name: Infest
Description:
Lifestealer infests the body of a target unit, becoming undetectable, and healing for a portion of his max hitpoints every second while inside. He can then explode from the host body, dealing damage to nearby enemies. If the infested unit is an enemy creep or a neutral creep, he can take control of the unit's ability to move and attack. Does not work on enemy heroes.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Assimilate
Description:
Lifestealer swallows an allied hero, allowing them to hide within him. Any healing Lifestealer receives is shared with the hero within. When an assimilated hero leaves Lifestealer, they erupt outward, damaging nearby enemies.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel

Name: Eject
Description: Ejects an Assimilated hero, damaging nearby enemies.

Name: Consume
Description: Lifestealer eats the host body from the inside out, exploding from within.

Name: Control
Description: Lifestealer seizes control of the host body's nervous system, allowing him to issue movement and attack orders from within.  Controlled units share Lifestealer's movement speed.  Cannot be used on heroes.

Name: Corpse Eater
Description: Lifestealer gains %bonus_hp_per_creep% HP whenever he kills a creep, and %bonus_hp_per_hero% whenever he kills a hero.

Name: Dragon Slave
Description: Lina channels the breath of a dragon, sending out a wave of fire that scorches every enemy in its path.

Name: Light Strike Array
Description: Summons a column of flames that damages and stuns enemies.

Name: Fiery Soul
Description: Grants bonus attack and movement speed each time Lina hits an enemy with a spell. Stacks with itself. Lasts %fiery_soul_stack_duration% seconds.

Name: Flame Cloak
Description: Grants Lina unobstructed movement and increases her spell damage and magic resistance. Grants max fiery soul stacks on activation.

Name: Laguna Blade
Description: Fires off a bolt of lightning at a single enemy unit, dealing massive damage.

Name: Slow Burn
Description: Lina's spells deal %total_damage_tooltip%% total damage. %damage_penalty_tooltip%% is dealt on impact and %burn_percent_tooltip_damage%% is dealt as burn damage over %burn_duration%s.

Name: Combustion
Description: Every %damage_threshold% damage Lina does to an enemy hero causes them to overheat, doing damage to their nearby allies. This effect can trigger multiple times off a single instance of damage. Overheated illusions do less damage.

Name: {s:bonus_fiery_soul_magic_resist}% Fiery Soul Magic Resist Per Stack
{s:bonus_barrier_pct}% Laguna Blade Damage into barrier
Description: Lasts {s:bonus_barrier_duration} seconds.

Name: +{s:bonus_target_crit_multiplier}% Crit On Targets Affected By Dragon Slave
Description: Only applies to Lina's attacks

Name: +{s:bonus_target_crit_multiplier}% Crit On Targets Affected By Spells
Description: Only applies to Lina's attacks. Lasts {s:bonus_target_crit_debuff_duration}s.

Name: Earth Spike
Description: Rock spikes burst from the earth along a straight path. Enemy units are hurled into the air, then are stunned and take damage when they fall.

Name: Hex
Description: Transforms an enemy unit into a harmless beast, with all special abilities disabled.

Name: Mana Drain
Description:
CHANNELED - Channels magical energy, taking mana and slowing enemies over time. If the enemy has no mana remaining, the slow is increased by %movespeed_bonus_when_empty_pct%%.

Can target allies to give them mana and movement speed at a %ally_pct%% rate.

Name: Finger of Death
Description: Rips at an enemy unit, trying to turn it inside-out. Deals massive damage and grows stronger with each life it consumes.

Name: +{s:bonus_damage_per_kill} Finger of Death Damage Per Kill
Earth Spike affects a 30 degree cone
+{s:value} Max Health Per Finger of Death Kill
To Hell and Back
Description: Lion gains %debuff_amp%% debuff duration and %spell_amp%% spell amplification for %duration%s after respawning.

Name: Sacred Arrow
Description: Fires a long-range arrow with deadly precision, which stuns and damages the first enemy unit it strikes. The stun duration ranges from %arrow_min_stun% to %arrow_max_stun% seconds, with bonus damage up to %arrow_bonus_damage% added, based on the distance the arrow travels to its target. Instantly kills the first non-ancient creep it hits.

Name: Moonlight Shadow
Description: Turns Mirana and all allied heroes invisible and grants bonus movement speed. If a hero is revealed, invisibility will restore after the fade delay as long as Moonlight Shadow's duration has not expired.

Name: Solar Flare
Description:
Gradually increases attack speed and damage of Mirana and all allied heroes, reaching maximum power after %max_damage_time%s.

Allies receive %ally_pct%% of the bonus.

Name: Leap
Description: Mirana leaps forward into battle, empowering herself with a ferocious roar that grants bonus attack and movement speed. Speed bonus lasts %leap_bonus_duration% seconds.

Name: Starstorm
Description: Calls down a wave of meteors to damage nearby enemy units. The closest enemy unit to Mirana in a %starfall_secondary_radius% radius will be struck a second time for %secondary_starfall_damage_percent%% of the damage.

Name: Selemene's Faithful
Description: Healing Lotuses are %bonus_lotus%% more effective on Mirana and her allies.

Name: +{s:bonus_extra_arrows} Multishot Sacred Arrows
Description: The extra arrows are launched in a cone shape, {s:bonus_extra_arrows_angle} degrees to the left and right of the original arrow, and cannot hit the same target.

Name: Moonlight Shadow gives +{s:bonus_evasion}% Evasion
Description: Evasion works at all times during the buff

Name: Waveform
Description: Morphling dissolves into liquid and surges forward, damaging enemy units in his path.  Morphling is invulnerable during Waveform and attacks all enemies it goes through with a penalty.

Name: Adaptive Strike (Agility)
Description:
Launches a surge of water toward an enemy unit, dealing base damage plus additional damage based on Morphling's agility times a multiplier.  If Morphling's agility is 50% higher than strength, the maximum agility multiplier is used. 

 Also puts Adaptive Strike (Strength) on a %shared_cooldown% second cooldown.

Name: Adaptive Strike (Strength)
Description:
Launches a surge of water toward an enemy unit, stunning the target based on Morphling's strength. If his strength is 50% higher than his agility, the maximum stun is dealt. 

 Also puts Adaptive Strike (Agility) on a %shared_cooldown% second cooldown.

Name: Attribute Shift (Agility Gain)
Description: Morphling shifts its form, pulling points from Strength and pouring them into Agility. The process is reversible.  Additional points in Attribute Shift increase the rate of stat change.

Name: Attribute Shift (Strength Gain)
Description: Morphling shifts its form, pulling points from Agility and pouring them into Strength. The process is reversible.  Additional points in Attribute Shift increase the rate of stat change.

Name: Ebb
Description: Morphling's Primary Attribute is now <font color='#9acd32'>Agility</font>

Name: Flow
Description: Morphling's Primary Attribute is now <font color='#ff0000'>Strength</font> and Attribute Shift can accelerate his cooldowns.

Name: Morph
Description: Morphling changes his form to match the targeted enemy, gaining their basic abilities. Can be toggled for the duration of the ability.

Name: Morph Replicate
Description: Toggles Morphling's form between his own and the replicated enemy.

Name: Hybrid
Description: Morphling creates a hybrid replication of a target allied hero, which can cast all of that hero's current, non-ultimate abilities. Enemies are able to see which unit is a hybrid.

Name: Accumulation
Description: Morphling receives %percent_to_increment%% of stat growth bonuses every half level instead of the full bonus at level up. Morphling receives +%bonus_all_stats_pct_tooltip%% bonus stats from All Attributes bonus from skill points in the Talent Tree.

Name: +{s:bonus_pct_damage}% Waveform Attack Damage And Applies On Hit Effects
Death Seeker
Description: Necrophos turns into a large Death Pulse towards the target unit's position. Once it arrives to the location, the Death Pulse spreads towards nearby enemies and allies.

Name: Death Pulse
Description: Necrophos releases a wave of death around him, dealing damage to enemy units and healing allied units.
AbilityDraftNote: Shard: Access Death Seeker by toggling auto-cast on Death Pulse.

Name: Heartstopper Aura
Description: Necrophos stills the hearts of his opponents, causing nearby enemy units to lose a percentage of their max health over time.

Name: Sadist
Description: Necrophos gains stacking regen for %regen_duration% seconds for each unit he kills. Hero kills multiply the effect.

Name: Ghost Shroud
Description: Necrophos slips into the realm that separates the living from the dead. Unable to attack or be attacked, he emits an aura that slows enemies around him. He takes additional magic damage in this form, but his restorative powers are amplified.
AbilityDraftNote: Ghost Shroud is removed as soon as you cast any magic immune spells (Bladefury, Rage, etc.)

Name: Reaper's Scythe
Description: Stuns the target enemy hero, then deals damage based on how much life it is missing. If Necrophos kills an enemy this way, he'll permanently gain Health and Mana Regen. Any kill under this effect is credited to Necrophos.

Name: Shadowraze
Description: Shadow Fiend razes the ground directly in front of him, dealing damage to enemy units in the area. Adds a stacking damage amplifier on the target that causes the enemy to take bonus Shadowraze damage per stack.

Name: Shadowraze
Description: Shadow Fiend razes the ground a short distance away from him, dealing damage to enemy units in the area. Adds a stacking damage amplifier on the target that causes the enemy to take bonus Shadowraze damage per stack.
AbilityDraftNote: Shadowraze has 3 charges and uses the mid-range Shadowraze.

Name: Shadowraze
Description: Shadow Fiend razes the ground a longer distance away from him, dealing damage to enemy units in the area. Adds a stacking damage amplifier on the target that causes the enemy to take bonus Shadowraze damage per stack.

Name: Necromastery
Description: Shadow Fiend steals the soul from units he kills, gaining bonus damage. On death, he releases %soul_release_tooltip%% of them from bondage.

Name: Presence of the Dark Lord
Description: Shadow Fiend's presence reduces the armor of nearby enemies.

Name: Feast of Souls
Description: Shadow Fiend gains Bonus Attack Speed for %duration% seconds. After the effect finishes, Shadow Fiend loses a fixed amount of souls.

Name: Requiem of Souls
Description:
Shadow Fiend gathers his captured souls to release them as lines of demonic energy. Units near Shadow Fiend when the souls are released can be damaged by several lines of energy. Any unit damaged by Requiem of Souls will be feared and have its movement speed and magic resistance reduced for %requiem_slow_duration% seconds for each line hit up to a maximum of %requiem_slow_duration_max%. Lines of energy are created for every soul captured through Necromastery.

Requiem of Souls is automatically cast whenever Shadow Fiend dies, regardless of its cooldown.
AbilityDraftNote: Must draft Necromastery to do damage.

Name: +{s:bonus_requiem_slow_duration}s Requiem Fear per line
Description: Max Fear duration increased by +{s:bonus_requiem_slow_duration_max}s

Name: Feast of Souls Grants +{s:bonus_cast_speed_pct}% Cast Speed
Void
Description: Creates a damaging void that slows an enemy unit, reduces its vision and deals damage. At night, Void also mini-stuns, interrupting channeling abilities, and its effects lasts longer.

Name: Crippling Fear
Description: Night Stalker horrifies all nearby enemies, causing them to become silenced and take damage over time while near him.  The effect lasts longer at night.

Name: Hunter in the Night
Description: Night Stalker is in his element at night, attacking and moving with great swiftness.

Name: Dark Ascension
Description: Night Stalker smothers the sun and summons instant darkness, so that he might use his powers at their fullest. Night Stalker gains flight and bonus damage during this time. Has unobstructed vision.

Name: Heart of Darkness
Description: During the night, Night Stalker's health regeneration is increased by %hp_regen_during_night_pct%%, and during the day it is decreased by %hp_regen_during_day_pct%%.

Name: Night Reign
Description: The game now starts at night instead of day. Night is longer than day.

Name: +{s:bonus_bonus_attack_speed_night} Hunter In The Night Attack Speed
+{s:bonus_bonus_status_resist_night}% Hunter in the Night Status Resistance
Hammer of Purity
Description: Omniknight imbues his hammer with holy power, causing his attack to deal pure damage based on a percentage of his base damage.

Name: Purification
Description: Instantly heals a friendly unit and damages all nearby enemy units.

Name: Heavenly Grace
Description:
Creates a divine barrier around an ally which grants them increased Status Resistance, Strength and Health Regeneration.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel

Name: Divine Sanction
Description: Causes affected enemies to deal less spell damage for a duration.

Name: Degen Aura
Description: Degenerates the movement capabilities of enemy units that stray too near.

Name: Healing Hammer
Description: Ability damage done to enemies by Omniknight heals him over time.

Name: Repel
Description: Grants Debuff Immunity with %magic_resist%% magic resistance to the target, as well as bonus Strength and HP Regen based on the amount of Debuffs on them.

Name: Guardian Angel
Description: Omniknight calls upon a Guardian Angel that grants immunity from physical damage to allied units in an area.

Name: +{s:bonus_base_damage}% Hammer of Purity Bonus Base Damage
Illusory Orb
Description: Puck launches a magic orb that floats in a straight path, damaging enemy units along the way. At any point, Puck may teleport to the orb's location using Ethereal Jaunt.
AbilityDraftNote: For Ability Draft only, Illusory Orb ability swaps with Ethereal Jaunt while the orb is in flight.

Name: Ethereal Jaunt
Description: Teleports Puck to a flying Illusory Orb.

Name: Puckish
Description: Whenever Puck disjoints an attack, it restores %mana_restore_base% + %mana_restore_pct%% of its max mana and %hp_restore_base% + %hp_restore_pct%% of its max health. Dodging a targeted spell projectile restores %dodged_spell_multiplier%x that amount.

Name: Waning Rift
Description: Puck teleports to the target location and releases a burst of faerie dust that deals damage and silences enemy units nearby.

Name: Phase Shift
Description: CHANNELED - Puck briefly shifts into another dimension where it is immune from harm.

Name: Dream Coil
Description: Creates a coil of volatile magic that latches onto enemy Heroes, damaging and leashing them.  If the enemy hero stretches the coil by moving too far away, it snaps, stunning and dealing additional damage.

Name: Meat Shield
Description: Pudge covers himself with a layer of flesh that blocks damage of any type taken from any source.

Name: Meat Hook
Description: Launches a bloody hook toward a unit or location. The hook will snag the first unit it encounters, dragging the unit back to Pudge, killing it if it's a non-ancient creep and dealing damage if it is an enemy otherwise.

Name: Rot
Description: A toxic cloud that deals intense damage and slows movement--harming not only enemy units but Pudge himself.

Name: Eject
Description: Ejects the swallowed allied hero inside of you.

Name: Dismember
Description: CHANNELED - Pudge chows down on an enemy unit, disabling it and dealing damage over time. Damage is increased by Pudge's Strength and heals him for the total amount. Pudge pulls the unit at a rate of %pull_units_per_second% units, up to a minimum of %pull_distance_limit% range.

Name: Flesh Heap
Description: Each time Pudge kills an enemy Hero, he permanently gains %flesh_heap_strength_buff_amount% bonus Strength.

Name: {s:bonus_flesh_heap_strength_buff_amount}x Flesh Heap and Meat Shield bonuses
Nether Blast
Description: An exploding pulse deals damage to enemies and structures in the area.  Deals %structure_damage_mod%% damage to structures.

Name: Decrepify
Description: A powerful banishing spell that slows a unit and renders it unable to attack or be attacked. Healing on affected allies is increased, while afflicted enemies take extra magic damage instead.

Name: Nether Ward
Description: Pugna places a Nether Ward at the target location. The ward will fire at any enemy hero who casts a spell dealing base damage plus the damage multiplier of the mana spent by the enemy hero.

Name: Life Drain
Description:
CHANNELED - When cast on an enemy, Pugna drains health from the target enemy unit to heal himself and granting vision over the target. If Pugna has full HP, and the enemy target is a Hero, Life Drain will restore mana instead.

When cast on an ally, Pugna will drain his own health into his ally.

Name: Oblivion Savant
Description: Pugna can cast spells and use items while channeling.

Name: Jetpack
Description: Clockwerk activates a jetpack, gaining flying movement, flying vision, and bonus movement speed. Clockwerk has a severely-limited turn rate during this time and cannot attack. Jetpack is cancelled upon casting Hookshot.

Name: Overclocking
Description: Supercharges Clockwerks abilities: Battery Assault affects all enemies in its range; Clockwerk's attack speed in Power Cogs is increased; Rocket Flares have a reduced cooldown and fire additional rockets to either side of the target; Hookshot stun radius and duration is increased; Jetpack moves faster. Clockwerk's movement and attack speed becomes slowed to a crawl after the duration runs out.

Name: Battery Assault
Description: Discharges high-powered shrapnel at random nearby enemy units, dealing minor magical damage and ministun. Deals double damage to creeps.

Name: Power Cogs
Description:
Forms a ring of energized cogs around Clockwerk, trapping any units that are near. Enemies outside the trap that touch a cog are knocked back, losing health and mana. Once a cog has delivered a shock, it will power down. Damage is increased by %mana_burn_as_damage_pct%% of the mana burned.

Cogs can be destroyed by enemy attacks, but Clockwerk can push them up to %projectile_distance% distance away with one hit.

Name: Rocket Flare
Description: Fires a global range flare that explodes over a given area. Upon impact, enemies in the area take damage and are briefly slowed. Rocket flare provides vision over the impact area for %duration% seconds.

Name: Hookshot
Description: Fires a grappling device rapidly at the target location.  If the hook hits a unit, Clockwerk launches himself into the target, stunning and dealing damage to everyone in a %stun_radius% radius around the hit target.  Any enemies Clockwerk collides with along the way are damaged and stunned.

Name: Armor Power
Description: Clockwerk's outgoing damage increases by %damage_per_armor%% per point of armor.

Name: Debuff Immunity Inside Power Cogs
Description: Also provides 50% magic resistance while Debuff Immune.

Name: Plasma Field
Description: Releases a wave of energetic plasma that grows in power as it expands, but also zaps on contraction, slowing and dealing damage to enemy units caught in its path. Damage and slow increases with distance from Razor. The Plasma Field hits each unit twice, once each direction.

Name: Static Link
Description: Creates a charged link between Razor and an enemy Hero, stealing damage from the target and giving it to Razor. Allows Razor to attack while moving with the link active.

Name: Storm Surge
Description: There's a chance when attacked, and always when targeted with a spell, to release a forked lightning that strikes the target and other nearby enemies, prioritizing the unit type of the attacker, dealing damage and slowing movement speed.

Name: Unstable Current
Description: Passively increases Razor's movement speed by %movespeed_per_level_pct%% per hero level.

Name: Eye of the Storm
Description: A powerful lightning storm strikes out at the enemy unit with the lowest health, dealing damage and reducing armor.

Name: Dynamo
Description: Razor gains %spell_amp_mult%% spell amplification for every %spell_amp_damage_divisor% points of attack damage.

Name: -{s:bonus_strike_interval}s Eye of the Storm Strike Interval
Creates A Second Plasma Field Delayed By {s:bonus_second_ring_delay}s
Description: The second plasma field does {s:bonus_second_ring_reduction}% less damage

Name: Sleeping Dart
Description: Fires a dart at the target enemy, putting them to sleep.  The target will wake up at the end of the duration or if they take too much damage. Upon waking up, the target takes damage and is slowed.

Name: Smoke Screen
Description: Throws down a smoke bomb, silencing enemies. Enemies attacking from the smoke or attacking allies within the smoke have a chance to miss their attacks.

Name: Blink Strike
Description: Teleports behind the target unit, momentarily slowing them and striking for bonus damage if it is an enemy.

Name: Cloak and Dagger
Description: Riki fades into the shadows, becoming invisible. When Riki attacks, he becomes visible.

Name: Backstab
Description: Every time Riki strikes his enemy from behind, he deals bonus damage based on his Agility.

Name: Permanent Invisibility
Description: Riki fades into the shadows, becoming invisible. When Riki attacks, he becomes visible. Grants bonus movement speed

Name: Tricks of the Trade
Description: CHANNELED - Riki phases out of the world while striking random enemy units from behind in an area around him. While phased out his attack damage is reduced, but his Agility greatly increases.

Name: +{s:bonus_agility_pct} Tricks of the Trade Agility Increase
Tricks of the Trade Applies a Basic Dispel
Description: Can be cast when rooted or leashed

Name: Burrowstrike
Description:
Sand King burrows into the ground and tunnels forward, damaging and stunning enemy units above him as he resurfaces. Adds Caustic Finale poison to heroes hit

Can be put on alt-cast to immediately cast in the desired direction, without walking towards the targeted location.

Name: Sand Storm
Description: Sand King creates a fearsome sandstorm that damages enemy units. The effect ends when Sand King leaves the area.

Name: Caustic Finale
Description: Sand King's attacks inject a venom that causes enemy units to violently explode when they die.

Name: Epicenter
Description: After a cast point of %abilitycastpoint% seconds, Sand King sends a disturbance into the earth, causing it to shudder violently. All enemies caught within range will take damage and become slowed. Each subsequent pulse increases the radius of damage dealt.

Name: Stinger
Description: Sand King strikes an area, performing an attack on all enemies in the area of effect, dealing extra damage to each. Enemies within an innermost radius of %inner_radius% take %inner_radius_bonus_damage_pct%% extra damage. Applies Caustic Finale and a slow to all enemies hit.

Name: {s:value}% Sand Storm Slow and Blind
Description: Enemy units in range of Sand Storm have their movement speed slowed by {s:value}% and miss {s:value}% of their attacks.

Name: Ether Shock
Description: Creates a cone of ethereal energy that strikes multiple enemy units.

Name: Hex
Description: Transforms an enemy unit into a harmless creature, disabling their attacks and abilities.

Name: Shackles
Description: CHANNELED - Magically binds an enemy unit so that it cannot move or attack, absorbing their life energy over time.

Name: Mass Serpent Ward
Description: Summons %ward_count% Serpent Wards to attack enemy units and structures. The Wards are immune to magic.

Name: Serpentine
Description: Creates a line of %count% Serpent Wards.

Name: Fowl Play
Description:
When taking lethal damage, Shadow Shaman receives a strong dispel and survives as a 1 HP chicken. Incoming damage is reduced to zero for %damage_reduction_duration%s.

Cooldown is reset upon respawning. DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel

Name: Seaborn Sentinel
Description: Slardar gains bonus movement speed, health regeneration, attack damage, and armor while in a puddle or river.

Name: Guardian Sprint
Description: Slardar slithers ahead, moving significantly faster and passing through units.

Name: Slithereen Crush
Description: Slams the ground, leaving a puddle of water, and stunning and damaging nearby enemy units.  After the stun, the affected units are slowed.

Name: Bash of the Deep
Description: After %attack_count% attacks, your next attack will bash the target. Deals double damage against creeps.
AbilityDraftNote: In Ability Draft, does stack with Skull Basher.

Name: Corrosive Haze
Description: Reduces enemy armor to amplify physical damage and provides True Sight and vision of the targeted unit, revealing invisibility. The enemy unit leaves a trail of water behind it for 8 seconds.

Name: Concussive Grenade
Description: Launches a grenade at the target area, dealing damage to enemies and knocking them and Sniper himself back. Enemies affected are disarmed and have their movement slowed after the knockback.

Name: Shrapnel
Description: Consumes a charge to launch a ball of shrapnel that showers the target area in explosive pellets. Enemies are subject to damage and slowed movement. Reveals the targeted area. Shrapnel charges restore every %abilitychargerestoretime% seconds.

Name: Headshot
Description: Sniper increases his accuracy, giving him a chance to deal extra damage and knock back his enemies. Knockback distance increases based on how close the enemy is to Sniper. Headshots briefly slow enemy movement and attack speed by %slow%%.

Name: Take Aim
Description: Increases armor, Headshot chance, and attack range. Slows you by %slow%% for the duration.

Name: Assassinate
Description: Sniper locks onto a target enemy unit and, after a short aiming duration, fires a devastating shot that deals Sniper's attack damage plus bonus damage at long range and mini-stuns the target. Whenever Sniper kills an enemy hero, Assassinate is refreshed.

Name: Keen Scope
Description: Increases Sniper's attack range.

Name: Spectral Dagger
Description: Spectre flings a dagger to draw a Shadow Path, dealing damage and slowing the movement speed of any enemies along the trail. Units hit by the dagger also trail a Shadow Path. While treading the path, Spectre phases through otherwise impassable terrain.

Name: Desolate
Description: Deals bonus damage whenever Spectre attacks an enemy that does not have any allied units within a %radius% radius around them.

Name: Dispersion
Description: Damage done to Spectre is reflected on her enemies, leaving her unharmed. The effect lessens with distance.
AbilityDraftNote: Haunt must also be drafted for Shard upgrade to work.

Name: Haunt
Description: Creates a spectral nemesis to attack each enemy hero. Illusions spawned from this ability follow the same rules as Shadow Step illusions and can also be swapped to by using Reality.

Name: Shadow Step
Description:
Creates a spectral nemesis to haunt a single visible enemy hero. At any moment during the duration, Spectre can use Reality to exchange places with any haunting illusion.

Haunt illusions are uncontrollable, take extra damage, and deal less damage than Spectre herself.  They ignore terrain.

Name: Reality
Description: Spectre exchanges places with a chosen Haunt.

Name: Spectral
Description: Spectre and her illusions are permanently phased.

Name: Electric Rave
Description: Grants Storm Spirit and allied heroes within %radius% AoE of him %charges% Overload charges. Provides 40 Attack Speed. Lasts up to %duration% seconds or until the charges are depleted.

Name: Static Remnant
Description: Creates an explosively charged image of Storm Spirit that lasts %abilityduration% seconds and will detonate and deal damage if an enemy unit comes near it.

Name: Electric Vortex
Description: A vortex that pulls an enemy unit to Storm Spirit's location.

Name: Overload
Description: Casting a spell creates an electrical charge, which is released in a burst on Storm's next attack, dealing damage and slowing nearby enemies.

Name: Ball Lightning
Description: Storm Spirit becomes volatile electricity, charging across the battlefield until he depletes his mana or reaches his target. The activation mana cost is %ball_lightning_initial_mana_base%+%ball_lightning_initial_mana_percentage%% of his total mana pool, and the cost per 100 units traveled is %ball_lightning_travel_cost_base%+%ball_lightning_travel_cost_percent%% of his total mana pool.  Damage is expressed in damage per 100 units traveled.

Name: Galvanized
Description: Storm Spirit gains a charge of %mp_per_kill% mana regeneration per kill. Loses %charges_per_death% charges per death. Leveling Ball Lightning gives Storm Spirit %charges_per_ult% bonus charges. Additionally every time he gains a charge he also gains %perma_mp_per_kill% Mana Regen permanently.

Name: {s:value} Distance Auto Remnant in Ball Lightning
Description: Every {s:value} distance travelled in Ball Lightning creates a Static Remnant.

Name: {s:value}x Overload Attack Bounce
Description: Bouncing attacks deal {s:bonus_overload_damage_pct}% damage.

Name: Storm Hammer
Description: Sven unleashes his magical gauntlet that deals damage and stuns enemy units in a small area around the target.

Name: Great Cleave
Description: Sven strikes with great force, cleaving all nearby enemy units with his attack.

Name: Warcry
Description: Sven's Warcry heartens his allied heroes for battle, increasing their armor and movement speed. Lasts %duration% seconds.

Name: God's Strength
Description: Sven channels his rogue strength, granting bonus damage and slow resistance for %abilityduration% seconds.

Name: Vanquisher
Description: Sven's attacks deal %bonus_damage_pct%% bonus damage to stunned enemies.

Name: Wrath of God
Description: Sven gains additional attack damage from Strength, but has decreased base damage.

Name: Gush
Description: Summons a gush of water to damage an enemy unit, reducing their movement speed and armor.

Name: Kraken Shell
Description:
Thickens Tidehunter's hide to passively block a portion of any incoming physical attack damage.

Does not stack with items that provide Damage Block.

Name: Anchor Smash
Description: Tidehunter swings his mighty anchor to attack and deal bonus damage to nearby enemies and reduce their attack damage.

Name: Ravage
Description: Slams the ground, causing tentacles to erupt in all directions, damaging and stunning all nearby enemy units.

Name: Tendrils of the Deep
Description: Tidehunter unleashes a targeted slew of tentacles that damage and stun enemies within reach. The tentacles deal %damage_pct%% of Ravage's damage and stun, with a range %range_pct%% of Ravage's radius.

Name: Dead in the Water
Description: Tidehunter attaches a heavy anchor to an enemy hero. The hero is leashed while attached to the anchor. Attempting to move more than %chain_length% units away from the anchor forces the hero to %max_movement_speed% move speed, dragging the anchor behind them. The anchor can be destroyed with %attacks_to_destroy% hero attacks.

Name: Krill Eater
Description: Tidehunter begins the game much smaller and with -%attack_range_base% attack range and -%anchor_smash_radius_base% Anchor Smash radius. Tidehunter grows larger with experience, gaining attacking range and Anchor Smash radius per level. Base Strength reduced, and Strength Gain increased.

Name: Blubber
Description:
Tidehunter's hide removes negative status effects if he takes more than %damage_cleanse% damage. Removes most debuffs, even if they are generally not purgable.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel

Name: 50% chance of Anchor Smash on attack
Defense Matrix
Description: Targets an allied unit, applying an all damage barrier to them that also provides Status Resistance.

Name: Keen Conveyance
Description: CHANNELED - Teleport to a target friendly structure. Level 2 allows teleporting to friendly units and Level 3 to friendly heroes.

Name: Eureka!
Description: Tinker gains %one_percent_tooltip%% item cooldown reduction per %int_per_one_cdr% Intelligence, up to a maximum of %max_cdr%%.

Name: Laser
Description: Fires an intense energy beam, damaging and blinding the target. Blinded targets miss all physical attacks.

Name: Shrink Ray
Description: Reduces the enemy target size and lowers their max health by 20% for %duration% seconds.

Name: Heat-Seeking Missile
Description: Launches rockets at the nearest visible heroes within %radius% range.

Name: March of the Machines
Description: Enlists an army of robotic minions to destroy enemy units in an area around Tinker.

Name: Rearm
Description: CHANNELED - Resets the cooldown on Tinker's abilities.
AbilityDraftNote: For abilities with charges, a single charge of the ability will be added everytime Rearm is cast.

Name: Warp Flare
Description:
Throws a flare towards an enemy, dealing damage, teleporting them away, rooting them and reducing their Cast and Attack Range for %debuff_duration% seconds.

The teleport location is always the ability's current cast range + %bonus_distance% from Tinker's position when he threw the flare.

Name: Rearm Grants {s:bonus_magic_resistance}% Bonus Magic Resistance
Description: Lasts for {s:bonus_armor_duration}s.

Name: Avalanche
Description: Bombards an area with rocks, continously doing small intervals of damage and stun to enemy units. Avalanche does %toss_damage_bonus_pct%% bonus damage to units being tossed

Name: Toss
Description: Grabs the nearest unit in a %grab_radius% radius around Tiny, ally or enemy, and launches it at the target unit or rune to deal damage where they land.

Name: Craggy Exterior
Description: Enemies that attack Tiny receive a stacking debuff that lowers their attack damage with each stack.

Name: Tree Grab
Description: Grabs a tree to whack enemies on the head for a limited number of attacks. Grants bonus attack range. Attacks deal more damage and fully splash on units along the way. The tree can be thrown, to deal your attack to a unit at a distance.
AbilityDraftNote: Scepter: Access Tree Volley by toggling auto-cast on Tree Grab.

Name: Tree Throw
Description: Throws the tree at the target unit, proccing your attack on it and splashing damage around the target.

Name: Tree Volley
Description: CHANNELED - Tiny channels to throw random trees within range towards the targeted area. Deals Tiny's attack damage to enemies in that area with each tree thrown.

Name: Grow
Description: Tiny gains craggy mass, increasing his attack damage, movement speed and armor, and toss power while slowing his attack speed.

Name: Rocksteady
Description: Tiny's attack speed can never go above or below %max_attack_speed%, but %attack_speed_to_damage%% of attack speed he would have received from items or buffs are converted into damage.

Name: Insurmountable
Description: Tiny gains Status and Slow Resistance from Strength.

Name: Toss Requires No Target
Description: Toss can target the ground as well as enemy units.

Name: Magic Missile
Description: Fires a magic missile at an enemy unit, stunning and dealing damage.

Name: Vengeance Aura
Description: Vengeful Spirit's presence increases the damage of nearby friendly heroes.

Name: Wave of Terror
Description: Vengeful Spirit lets loose a wicked cry, weakening the total attack damage and armor of enemies, and giving vision of the path ahead.

Name: Nether Swap
Description: Instantaneously swaps positions with a target Hero, friend or enemy. Nether Swap interrupts channeling abilities on the target. Enemy Swapped units take damage. Vengeful Spirit and allied swapped units gain a barrier equal to the damage dealt.

Name: Soul Strike
Description: Vengeful Spirit's ranged attacks behave as if they were melee attacks.

Name: Retribution
Description: Whenever an enemy hero kills Vengeful Spirit, they get a debuff until their next death, causing Vengeful Spirit to deal %bonus_damage%% bonus damage to them.

Name: Wave Of Terror Steals {s:bonus_steal_pct}% Of Reduced Damage And Armor
Venomancer Scepter
Description: Creates a %radius% AoE pool of poison at the target location, dealing another instance of Poison Nova damage and slows by 20%. If an enemy dies in the area, a Plague Ward is spawned.

Name: Venomous Gale
Description: Launches a ball of venom in a line, poisoning enemy units so that they take both initial damage and damage over time, as well as suffering slowed movement.  Venomous Gale deals damage every 3 seconds over its duration.

Name: Poison Sting
Description: Adds poison damage to Venomancer's normal attacks and slowing movement speed.

Name: Plague Ward
Description: Summons a plague ward to attack enemy units and structures. The ward is immune to magic. Wards gain the Poison Sting level from Venomancer, dealing 50% of the full damage.

Name: Noxious Plague
Description: Infects an enemy with a deadly plague that does an initial burst of damage and additional damage over time based on the unit's maximum health. The plague slows the target and nearby enemies based on their distance to the target. When the target dies or the debuff expires, all nearby enemies are infected with a noncommunicable version of the plague.

Name: Poison Nova
Description: Whenever Venomancer or an enemy with Venomous Gale dies, a spreading ring of poison erupts. Enemies hit by the poison will take non-lethal magic damage over time and have their magic resistance reduced. This effect can trigger every %trigger_cd% seconds and cannot be refreshed.

Name: Latent Toxicity
Description: Applies a weak poison that minorly slows and deals damage to its target. If this poison is dispelled in any way, the target will receive a large amount of damage and be stunned.

Name: Septic Shock
Description: Venomancer's attacks deal extra damage based on how many debuffs the attack target has. Extra damage is dealt as magical damage. Only counts debuffs from Venomancer or his Plague Wards.

Name: Noxious Plague Aura reduces {s:bonus_attack_slow} Attack Speed
Gale Creates Plague Wards
Description: When Venomous Gale impacts enemy Heroes, it creates {s:bonus_create_wards} Plague Wards around them.

Name: Poison Attack
Description: Intensifies Viper's venom, adding an effect to his normal attack that applies a stacking movement speed slow and magic resistance deduction while dealing damage over time. Stacks up to %max_stacks% times.

Name: Nethertoxin
Description: Viper releases a Nethertoxin at the targeted area. Units in that area take an increasing damage over time based on how long they remain in it. Units in it have their attack speed slowed.

Name: Corrosive Skin
Description: Viper exudes an infectious toxin that damages and slows the attack speed of any enemy that damages it in a %max_range% radius. The acid exudate also increases Viper's resistance to magic.

Name: Predator
Description: Viper's attacks deal an additional instance of physical damage per missing health percentage of the target hero, equal to %damage_base% + %damage_per_level% per Viper's level.

Name: Viper Strike
Description: Viper slows the targeted enemy unit's movement and attack speed while also disabling their passives and dealing poison damage over time. The slowing effect reduces over the duration of the poison.

Name: Nosedive
Description: Viper slams into the ground, splattering each enemy in a %corrosive_radius% AoE for %effect_duration% seconds with the effect of Corrosive Skin.

Name: The Swarm
Description: Weaver launches a swarm of %count% young Weavers that latch on any enemy unit in their path, attacking and reducing armor until it is killed.

Name: Shukuchi
Description: Weaver shifts out of visibility, gaining max movement speed --doing harm to any enemies it passes through.

Name: Geminate Attack
Description: Allows Weaver to dispatch two attacks at once.

Name: Time Lapse
Description:
Weaver warps backward to whatever position it was in five seconds earlier--regaining the HP and mana from that time. No effect on cooldown, gold or experience.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel

Name: Rewoven
Description: Every time Weaver casts an ability, he gains %attack_range_increase_per_stack% attack range for %duration%s. This effect stacks independently.

Name: Gale Force
Description: Vector Targeted. Summons a strong wind that pushes all enemies in the target area towards the target direction.

Name: Shackleshot
Description: Shackles the target to an enemy unit or tree in a line directly behind it.  If no unit or tree is present, the stun duration is reduced to %fail_stun_duration%.

Name: Powershot
Description: CHANNELED - Windranger charges her bow for up to %abilitychanneltime% second for a single powerful shot, which slows and deals more damage the longer it is charged. The arrow damages enemies along its path. For each enemy that Powershot hits, its damage and slow power is reduced.

Name: Windrun
Description: Increases movement speed and adds evasion from all physical attacks.

Name: Focus Fire
Description: Windranger channels the wind to gain %bonus_attack_speed% additional attack speed against a single enemy unit or structure, though with a reduction to her attack damage.  Extra damage from secondary item effects is not reduced.

Name: Focus Fire Cancel
Description: End your Focus Fire early.

Name: Focus Fire Kills Advance Cooldown by {s:bonus_cooldown_reduction_per_kill}s
Description: Triggers if Focus Fired unit dies, regardless of killer.

Name: Easy Breezy
Description: Windranger's movement speed cannot be lower than %min_movespeed% and can reach %max_movespeed%.

Name: Paralyzing Cask
Description: Launches a cask of paralyzing powder that ricochets between enemy units, stunning and damaging those it hits. Deals %creep_damage_pct%% damage to creeps.

Name: Voodoo Restoration
Description: Witch Doctor focuses his magic to heal nearby allied units, costing Witch Doctor mana every second Voodoo Restoration is active.

Name: Maledict
Description: Curses all enemy Heroes in a small area, causing them to take a set amount of damage each second, as well as bursts of damage every 4 seconds based on how much health they have lost since the curse began.

Name: Death Ward
Description: CHANNELED - Summons a deadly ward to attack enemy heroes within its attack range. Lasts a maximum of %abilitychanneltime% seconds. Death Ward has %bonus_accuracy%% bonus accuracy.

Name: Voodoo Switcheroo
Description: Turns Witch Doctor into a Death Ward briefly with reduced attack speed. He is hidden during this time.

Name: Gris-Gris
Description:
Witch Doctor gets a Gris-Gris, an item that cannot be dropped or placed in the backpack.
