When the owner dies, %death_gold_lost_reduction_pct_tooltip%% of the gold lost from death is added to the item, and will be refunded when the item is consumed. The value of the Gris-Gris is increased by 1 every %gold_tick_interval_tooltip%s.

Right-click to consume and permanently remove the item.

Name: +{s:value}% Target Max Health Voodoo Restoration Heal
Heavenly Jump
Description: Zeus performs a Heavenly Jump, leaping forward and shocking the closest visible nearby enemy (prioritizing heroes), dealing damage as well as reducing their movement and attack speed. Zeus gets 900 unobstructed vision around him for 3 seconds.

Name: Arc Lightning
Description: Hurls a bolt of lightning that leaps through nearby enemy units that deal damage.
AbilityDraftNote: Shard: Lightning Hands is hidden in the ability panel when Shard is acquired, but can be enabled and disabled by activating the Alternate Cast on Arc Lightning.

Name: Lightning Bolt
Description: Calls down a bolt of lightning to strike an enemy unit, causing damage and a mini-stun. When cast, Lightning Bolt briefly provides unobstructed vision and True Sight around the target in a %sight_radius_night% radius. Can be cast on the ground, affecting the closest enemy hero in %spread_aoe% range.

Name: Nimbus
Description: Creates a storm cloud anywhere on the map that automatically casts Lightning Bolt on nearby enemies.

Name: Static Field
Description: Zeus shocks any enemy that he attacks or is hit by his abilities, causing damage equal to a percentage of their current health.
AbilityDraftNote: Static Field is associated to this ability and doesn't affect abilities other than Zeus'.

Name: Thundergod's Wrath
Description:
Strikes all enemy heroes with a bolt of lightning, dealing damage, no matter where they may be.

Thundergod's Wrath also provides True Sight around each hero struck. If an enemy hero is invisible, it takes no damage, but the True Sight is still created at that hero's location.
AbilityDraftNote: Nimbus requires Lightning Bolt to be drafted for damage.

Name: Lightning Hands
Description: Zeus gains bonus attack speed and his attacks create Arc Lightnings that deal a percentage of its damage. Can be toggled off to stop this effect.

Name: Spawn Spiderlings
Description: Broodmother injects her young into an enemy unit, dealing damage and slowing them for %slow_duration% seconds. The spiderlings will hatch if the target is killed while under this influence.

Name: Poison Sting
Description: Slows enemies with each attack.

Name: Spawn Spiderling
Description: Applies debuff on attack. If debuffed unit dies, a spiderling will spawn.

Name: Spin Web
Description:
Spins a large web that grants Broodmother a passive movement speed increase and increases her Turn Rate, while in its vicinity, as well as giving free movement.

Spin Web charges restore every %abilitychargerestoretime% seconds, with a max of %AbilityCharges% charges.

Spin Web can be cast from anywhere as long as the new web touches an existing web. Webs never expire, and can be manually destroyed. When the maximum limit of webs is exceeded, the oldest web disappears.

Name: Spider's Milk
Description: Whenever Broodmother kills a unit, she and all units under her control in a %kill_heal_aoe% radius receive a buff that heals them for a percentage of the victims health every %tick_rate% seconds. Healing from creeps is reduced by %kill_creeps_penalty%%.

Name: Silken Bola
Description: Deals impact damage, then slows the target and causes them to miss some attacks. Units that attack the target deal bonus magic damage.

Name: Incapacitating Bite
Description: Broodmother's venom cripples enemy units, causing her attacks to slow and giving the affected unit a chance to miss its attacks and extra damage from attacks.

Name: Insatiable Hunger
Description: A violent lust for vital fluids increases Broodmother's attack damage and gives her a vampiric attack. Lifesteal from creeps is reduced by %creep_lifesteal_reduction_pct%%.

Name: Spinner's Snare
Description: Broodmother may create up to %count% invisible web lines touching any existing web. Enemy Heroes that cross the web line will spring the trap, becoming rooted, revealed in fog, and take damage over time.  Multiple Heroes can trip on the same line until it's destroyed after being initially triggered.  Broodmother's team is alerted via the minimap when an enemy has triggered the snare.

Name: Destroy Spin Web
Description: Destroys the selected Spin Web.

Name: Wraithfire Blast
Description: Wraith King sears an enemy unit with spectral fire, dealing damage and stunning, then dealing damage over time and slowing the target.

Name: Bone Guard
Description: Gains a Charge for every 2 units killed. Activate to spend all charges, summoning skeletons that respawn once when killed. Skeletons benefit from Vampiric Spirit's lifesteal.

Name: Spectral Blade
Description: Curses units that Wraith King attacks, dealing a flat amount of damage and a percentage of the attack damage again after a delay. Vampiric Spirit's lifesteal applies to the curse damage and a unit cannot be cursed again for a short period of time.

Name: Mortal Strike
Description: Wraith King passively deals bonus damage on an attack with a cooldown.

Name: Reincarnation
Description: Wraith King's form regroups after death, allowing him to resurrect when killed in battle.  Upon death, enemy units in a %slow_radius% radius are slowed. Can be self-cast to kill Wraith King instantly.

Name: Vampiric Spirit
Description: Grants Wraith King Lifesteal. When slain Wraith King turns into a free pathing Wraith with Bonus Attack and Movement Speed for a short duration, delaying his death.

Name: Reincarnation Casts Wraithfire Blast
Description: Instead of being slowed, all enemy units within 900 range have the current level of Wraithfire Blast cast on them when Reincarnation triggers.

Name: Shadow Strike
Description: Hurls a poisoned dagger which deals large initial damage, and then deals damage over time. The poisoned unit has its movement speed slowed for %duration% seconds.  An instance of damage is dealt every %damage_interval% seconds.

Name: Blink
Description: Short distance teleportation that allows Queen of Pain to move in and out of combat.

Name: Scream Of Pain
Description: The Queen of Pain lets loose a piercing scream around her, damaging nearby enemies.

Name: Sonic Wave
Description: Creates a gigantic wave of sound in front of Queen of Pain, dealing heavy damage to all enemy units in its wake and pushing them back.

Name: Masochist
Description: Queen of Pain has bonus Spell Amplification but a percentage of her spell damage is reflected back to her.

Name: Succubus
Description: Queen of Pain gains Spell Lifesteal that increases with proximity to her enemies.

Name: Bondage
Description: Whenever an enemy within %radius% range deals spell damage to Queen of Pain, she returns %spell_reflect_pct%% of the damage dealt.

Name: +{s:bonus_attack_speed} Attack Speed against Shadow Striked units
Inner Vitality
Description: Unlocks the regenerative power of a friendly unit, with healing based upon its primary attribute. If the target is below 35%, it will heal faster.  Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.

Name: Inner Fire
Description: In a fiery rage, knocks all nearby enemies away from you to a fixed distance, dealing damage and silencing them.

Name: Burning Spear
Description: Huskar sets his spears aflame, dealing damage over time with his regular attack.  Multiple attacks will stack additional damage.  Each attack drains some of Huskar's health.

Name: Berserker's Blood
Description: Huskar's injuries feed his power, giving increased attack speed, magic resistance and health regen based on missing health. Health regen is a percentage of your strength.

Name: Blood Magic
Description: Huskar does not have mana. Mana costs of items are converted into health costs.

Name: Life Break
Description:
Huskar draws upon his health to break an enemy's life, leaping at a target to shatter a percentage of that hero's current health and slow both their movement and attack speed.  While leaping, Huskar is Debuff Immune and has 60% increased magic resistance.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Dual Breath
Description: An icy blast followed by a wave of fire launches out in a path in front of Jakiro. The ice slows enemies, while the fire delivers damage over time.

Name: Ice Path
Description: Creates a path of ice that stuns and damages enemies that touch it.

Name: Liquid Fire
Description: Jakiro burns his enemies in an area of effect with fire added to his attack, while slowing their attacks.
AbilityDraftNote: Shard does NOT grant Liquid Frost ability.

Name: Liquid Frost
Description: Jakiro's attacks chill his enemies, slowing movement for %duration% seconds and increasing damage taken from Jakiro's attacks and abilities. This effect does not apply to buildings.

Name: Macropyre
Description: Jakiro exhales a wide line of lasting flames, which deals damage per second to any enemy units caught in the fire.

Name: +{s:bonus_stun_duration}s Ice Path Duration
Description: Increases both stun and path duration.

Name: Double Trouble
Description: Jakiro's attacks launch an attack from each head, but deal %attack_damage_reduction%% less damage each.

Name: Sticky Napalm
Description: Drenches an area in sticky oil, amplifying damage from Batrider's attacks and abilities and slowing the movement speed and turn rate of enemies.  Additional casts of Sticky Napalm continue to increase damage, up to %max_stacks% stacks. Applies a small amount of damage with each cast.

Name: Smoldering Resin
Description: Batrider's attacks apply a debuff that deals %tick_attack_damage_pct%% of the attack damage every %tick_rate%s for %total_ticks%s.

Name: Stoked
Description: Batrider gains Move Speed and Spell Amplification when displacing enemies.

Name: Flamebreak
Description: Hurls an explosive cocktail that explodes when it reaches the target location, knocking back, slowing and dealing damage over time to enemies in the area.

Name: Firefly
Description: Batrider takes to the skies, laying down a trail of flames from the air.  The fire damages any enemies it touches, and destroys trees below Batrider.

Name: Flaming Lasso
Description: Lassoes an enemy and drags them in Batrider's wake. Dragged units cannot move, attack, or use abilities.  Teleporting or blinking will break the lasso.

Name: Fatal Bonds
Description: Binds several enemy units together, causing a percentage of the damage dealt to one of them to be felt by the others.

Name: Shadow Word
Description: Warlock whispers an incantation, casting a spell on a unit that makes it deal damage to nearby enemy units and heal nearby ally units. Target Unit will also heal or be damaged depending on whether they are ally or enemy.

Name: Upheaval
Description: CHANNELED - A powerful slowing and damaging current that grows stronger as it's channeled. Lasts up to %abilitychanneltime% seconds. Enemies are slowed for %duration% seconds after leaving the area or the spell ends.

Name: Chaotic Offering
Description: Summons a Golem from the depths, stunning enemies for %stun_duration% seconds. The Golem lives %golem_duration% seconds, takes reduced damage from spells, has increased Slow Resistance, has Permanent Immolation and Flaming Fists on attack.

Name: Flaming Fists
Description: Deals extra damage to nearby units when attacking.

Name: Permanent Immolation
Description: Burns the Golem's nearby enemy units, dealing damage per second.

Name: Eldritch Explosion
Description: Shortly after dying, a burst of magic damage is dealt to all enemies in a small area. Does %explosion_nonhero_reduce%% less damage to non-hero targets.

Name: Eldritch Summoning
Description: Whenever an enemy unit dies while afflicted by one or more of Warlock's abilities, a minor imp is summoned that lasts for %minor_imp_duration% seconds and explodes on death. Imps will automatically seek out nearby units, favoring fatally bonded heroes, and will explode when reaching their prey.

Name: Black Grimoire
Description: Grants Warlock the item Black Grimoire, which can be consumed to gain experience for each kill Warlock participated in. Starts with 1 charge.

Name: 80% Magic Resistance for Chaotic Offering Golems
+{s:value} Upheaval Attack Speed per second on Allies
Description: Maximum of +70 Attack Speed

Name: Berserk Potion
Description:
Alchemist throws a potion at an ally, applying a basic dispel and giving them attack speed, movement speed and HP regen.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Acid Spray
Description: Sprays high-pressure acid across a target area. Enemy units who step across the contaminated terrain take damage per second and have their armor reduced.

Name: Unstable Concoction
Description: Alchemist brews up an unstable concoction that he can throw at an enemy hero, to stun and deal damage in an area around the explosion. The longer the concoction brews, the more damage it deals and the longer the stun. Alchemist is faster while charging the concoction. After %brew_time% seconds, the brew reaches its maximum damage and stun time. However, after %brew_explosion% seconds, the concoction will explode on Alchemist himself if not thrown.

Name: Unstable Concoction Throw
Description: Throw it before it blows up!

Name: Greevil's Greed
Description: Alchemist synthesizes additional gold from his enemies and bounty runes. With each kill, Alchemist earns base bonus gold and extra bonus gold. If Alchemist kills another unit which yields gold within the next %duration% seconds, an additional instance of Extra Bonus Gold is added to the total. Additionally, causes bounty runes to yield more gold.
AbilityDraftNote: Chemical Rage Aghanim's Scepter has been moved to Greevil's Greed for Ability Draft. Use Aghanim's Scepter on an allied hero to grant them all Aghanim's Scepter upgrades. When you have a Scepter of your own, you will gain bonus damage and spell amplification for each gifted Scepter.

Name: Chemical Rage
Description:
Alchemist causes his Ogre to enter a chemically induced rage, reducing base attack cooldown and increasing movement speed and health regeneration.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
AbilityDraftNote: Also grants Greevil's Greed ability.

Name: Corrosive Weaponry
Description: Alchemist coats his weapons with an acid that applies a stacking slow and base attack damage reduction to enemies hit.

Name: Acid Spray grants armor to allies
Crypt Swarm
Description: Sends a swarm of winged beasts to savage enemy units in front of Death Prophet.

Name: Silence
Description: Fires a projectile that prevents enemy units in a target area from casting spells.

Name: Witchcraft
Description: Death Prophet's occult knowledge deepens with experience, gaining %movement_speed_pct_per_level%% movement speed per level, and %cooldown_reduction_pct_per_level%% spell cooldown reduction per level.

Name: Spirit Siphon
Description: Creates a spirit link between Death Prophet and an enemy unit, draining health from the enemy.

Name: Exorcism
Description:
Unleashes evil spirits to drain the life of nearby enemy units and structures. Spirits need to return back to Death Prophet in order to attack again. At the end of the spell's duration, Death Prophet is healed in proportion to the damage dealt. Deals 50% damage to buildings. Lasts %abilityduration% seconds.
Increases Death Prophet's movement speed while active.

Name: Spirit Collector
Description: Hero deaths empower your next Exorcism.

Name: Mourning Ritual
Description: Death Prophet delays a percentage of incoming damage, taking the damage in even intervals over a short duration.

Name: Earthshock
Description: Ursa leaps forward %hop_distance% units and slams the earth, causing a powerful shock to damage and slow all enemy units in a nearby area for %abilityduration% seconds.

Name: Overpower
Description: Using his skill in combat, Ursa gains increased attack speed and slow resistance for a number of subsequent attacks.

Name: Fury Swipes
Description: Ursa's claws dig deeper wounds in the enemy, causing consecutive attacks to the same enemy to deal more damage.  If the same target is not attacked after %bonus_reset_time% seconds, the bonus damage is lost.

Name: Enrage
Description:
Ursa goes into a frenzy, providing damage reduction and status resistance. Removes any existing debuffs.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel

Name: Maul
Description: Ursa gains bonus damage equal to a percentage of his Current HP.

Name: Bear Down
Description: Debuffs inflicted by Ursa last longer.

Name: Shuriken Toss
Description: Hurls a deadly shuriken at an enemy unit, dealing damage and slowing the target's Movement Speed by %slow%% for %slow_duration%s.  The shuriken will bounce to any Tracked units who are within a %bounce_aoe% radius of each other.

Name: Jinada
Description: Bounty Hunter plans his next hit, dealing bonus damage and stealing some unreliable gold.

Name: Shadow Walk
Description: Bounty Hunter becomes invisible and gains the ability to move through other units until he attacks or uses an ability.  If he breaks the invisibility with an attack, that attack will stun the target for a short duration.
AbilityDraftNote: Shard: Access Friendly Shadow by toggling auto-cast on Shadow Walk.

Name: Friendly Shadow
Description: Applies Shadow Walk and all of its bonuses to the target ally. Allied fade time is %fade_time%s. Does not break Bounty Hunter's invisibility when cast.

Name: Track
Description: Tracks an enemy hero, granting True Sight of the target, increasing the damage they take and providing information on how much gold it is carrying. Bounty Hunter moves fast when near the tracked unit. If the target dies, Bounty Hunter and nearby heroes collect a bonus bounty of gold. Casting Track does not take you out of invisibility.

Name: Cutpurse
Description: Bounty Hunter steals gold when targeting enemy heroes with his abilities or items.

Name: Big Game Hunter
Description: When getting a kill or assist on an enemy that has a killing streak, Bounty Hunter receives %bonus_killstreak_bounty%% extra gold.

Name: Arcane Curse
Description: Curses the target area, causing enemy heroes to take damage over time and slowing their movement speed. If a target casts a spell, they are silenced for a short period. The duration is paused as long as the target is silenced.

Name: Glaives of Wisdom
Description: Silencer enchants his glaives with his wisdom, stealing his target's Intelligence with each hit and dealing additional damage based on his Intelligence. After %stacks_for_silence% attacks on the same target, that enemy will be silenced for %silence_duration% seconds.

Name: Last Word
Description: Enemies within %radius% range of Silencer are slowed and damaged every second for each Silence they have on them.

Name: Global Silence
Description: Silencer stops all sound, preventing enemy heroes and units on the map from casting spells.

Name: Brain Drain
Description: If Silencer kills an enemy hero, he permanently steals %permanent_int_steal_amount% Intelligence.

Name: {s:bonus_bounce_count} Glaives of Wisdom Bounce
Description: Glaives of Wisdom Bounce to targets withing a {s:bonus_bounce_range} range.

Name: Charge of Darkness
Description:
Spirit Breaker fixes his sight on an enemy unit and starts charging through all objects, starting at %min_movespeed_bonus_pct%% of the bonus speed and reaching his max speed after %windup_time%s.

All enemy units passed through and the targeted unit will be hit by a Greater Bash. If the targeted unit dies, Spirit Breaker will change his target to the nearest enemy unit to that location.
AbilityDraftNote: No other units will be hit by Greater Bash if it's not drafted as well. Target of Charge of Darkness will be stunned on impact even without Greater Bash.

Name: Bulldoze
Description: Spirit Breaker gains movement speed and status resistance to ram through enemies. Can be used while charging.

Name: Empowering Haste
Description: Causes Spirit Breaker to gain power with higher movement speed. His presence increases the movement speed of nearby allied units. Can be cast to improve the movement speed bonus for %duration% seconds.

Name: Greater Bash
Description: Gives a chance to stun and knockback an enemy unit on an attack. Deals a percentage of movement speed as damage.
AbilityDraftNote: In Ability Draft, does stack with Skull Basher.

Name: Nether Strike
Description: Spirit Breaker slips into the nether realm, reappearing next to his hapless victim. Upon reappearing, a Greater Bash of the current level occurs and deals bonus damage. Knocks back for double the normal distance.
AbilityDraftNote: Greater Bash must be drafted for stun.  Bonus damage still applies without Greater Bash.

Name: Planar Pocket
Description: Barathrum distorts the fabric of planar space, increasing his own magic resistance and redirecting enemy hero spells in a radius towards him.

Name: Herd Mentality
Description: The hero on your team whose level is lower than anybody else's on your team gains %xp_gain_rate%% more experience.

Name: Quas
Description: Allows manipulation of ice elements.

Name: Wex
Description: Allows manipulation of storm elements.

Name: Exort
Description: Allows manipulation of fire elements.

Name: Invoked Spell
Description: Casting Invoke will replace this slot with one of ten unique spells based on Invoker's currently active <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>, <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>, and <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font> buffs.

Name: Invoked Spell
Description: Casting Invoke will replace this slot with one of ten unique spells based on Invoker's currently active <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>, <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>, and <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font> buffs.

Name: Invoke
Description:
Combines the properties of the elements currently being manipulated to create a new spell for Invoker to use. Invoke cooldown is reduced by %cooldown_reduction_per_orb% seconds for each orb level.

Click the help button to see the list of possible spells.

Name: Attribute Bonus
Description: Improves all attributes per point spent

Name: Cold Snap
Description: Invoker draws the heat from an enemy, chilling them to their very core for a duration based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>. The enemy will take damage and be briefly frozen. Further damage taken in this state will freeze the enemy again, dealing bonus damage and healing invoker. The enemy can only be frozen so often, but the freeze cooldown decreases based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>.

Name: Ghost Walk
Description: Invoker manipulates the ice and electrical energies around him, rendering his body invisible and gaining health and mana regen. The elemental imbalance created as a consequence slows nearby enemies based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>, and slows Invoker as well based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>.

Name: Tornado
Description:
Unleashes a fast moving tornado that picks up enemy units in its path, suspending them helplessly in the air shortly before allowing them to plummet to their doom. Travels further based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>. Holds enemies in the air for a duration based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>. Deals base damage plus added damage based on levels in <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: E.M.P.
Description: Invoker builds up a charge of electromagnetic energy at a targeted location which automatically detonates after %delay% seconds. The detonation covers an area, draining mana based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>. Deals damage for each point of mana drained.  If EMP drains mana from an enemy hero, Invoker gains %self_mana_restore_pct%% of the mana drained.

Name: Alacrity
Description: Invoker infuses an ally with an immense surge of energy, increasing their attack speed based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font> and their damage based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>.

Name: Chaos Meteor
Description: Invoker pulls a flaming meteor from space onto the targeted location. Upon landing, the meteor rolls forward, constantly dealing damage based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>, and rolling further based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>. Units hit by the meteor will also be set on fire for a short time, receiving additional damage based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>.

Name: Sun Strike
Description: Sends a catastrophic ray of fierce energy from the sun at any targeted location, incinerating all enemies standing beneath it once it reaches the earth. Deals damage based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>, however this damage is spread evenly over all enemies hit.

Name: Forge Spirit
Description: Invoker forges a spirit embodying the strength of fire and fortitude of ice. Damage and armor are based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font> while attack range, health, and duration are based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>. The elemental's scorching attack is capable of melting the armor of enemy heroes. Spawns two spirits when Quas and Exort are at least level 4.

Name: Melting Strike
Description: Melts away the armor of heroes hit by the spirit's attack. Each successive hit increases the amount of armor melted.

Name: Ice Wall
Description: Generates a wall of solid ice directly in front of Invoker for a duration based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>. The bitter cold emanating from it greatly slows nearby enemies based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font> and deals damage each second based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>.

Name: Deafening Blast
Description: Invoker unleashes a mighty sonic wave in front of him, dealing damage to any enemy unit it collides with based on the level of <font color='#cabe68'>Exort</font>. The sheer impact from the blast is enough to knock those enemy units back for a duration based on the level of <font color='#7998b5'>Quas</font>, then disarm their attacks for a duration based on the level of <font color='#d671a9'>Wex</font>.

Name: Mastermind
Description: When Invoker denies a lane creep, he gets %xp_on_deny_percent%% of the XP.

Name: Cold Snap (AD)
Description: Invoker draws the heat from an enemy, chilling them to their very core for a duration. The enemy will take damage and be briefly frozen. Further damage taken in this state will freeze the enemy again, dealing bonus damage. The enemy can only be frozen so often, but the freeze cooldown decreases as the level goes up.

Name: Ghost Walk (AD)
Description: Invoker manipulates the ice and electrical energies around him, rendering his body invisible. The elemental imbalance created as a consequence slows nearby enemies, and slows Invoker as well based on the level.

Name: Tornado (AD)
Description:
Unleashes a fast moving tornado that picks up enemy units in its path, suspending them helplessly in the air shortly before allowing them to plummet to their doom. Travels further based on the level and holds enemies in the air for a duration.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: E.M.P. (AD)
Description: Invoker builds up a charge of electromagnetic energy at a targeted location which automatically detonates after %delay% seconds. The detonation covers an area, draining mana. Deals damage for each point of mana drained.  If EMP drains mana from an enemy hero, Invoker gains 50% of the mana drained.

Name: Alacrity (AD)
Description: Invoker infuses an ally with an immense surge of energy, increasing their attack speed and their damage.

Name: Sun Strike (AD)
Description: Sends a catastrophic ray of fierce energy from the sun at any targeted location, incinerating all enemies standing beneath it once it reaches the earth. Damage is spread evenly over all enemies hit.

Name: Forge Spirit (AD)
Description: Invoker forges a spirit embodying the strength of fire and fortitude of ice. The elemental's scorching attack is capable of melting the armor of enemy heroes.

Name: Chaos Meteor (AD)
Description: Invoker pulls a flaming meteor from space onto the targeted location. Upon landing, the meteor rolls forward, constantly dealing damage and rolling further based on the level. Units hit by the meteor will also be set on fire for a short time.

Name: Ice Wall (AD)
Description: Generates a wall of solid ice directly in front of Invoker for a duration. The bitter cold emanating from it greatly slows nearby enemies and deals damage each second.

Name: Deafening Blast
Description: Invoker unleashes a mighty sonic wave in front of him, dealing damage to any enemy unit it collides with. The sheer impact from the blast is enough to knock those enemy units back for a duration then disarm their attacks for a duration.

Name: Radial Deafening Blast
Description: Releases {s:bonus_radial_count} additional Deafening Blasts around Invoker in a circular pattern.  An enemy can only be hit once per cast.

Name: Strafe
Description:
Clinkz gains attack speed and has bonus attack range. Any current Skeleton Archers within a %strafe_skeleton_radius% radius of Clinkz also gain bonus attack range and %archer_attack_speed_pct%% of the attack speed bonus.

Casting Strafe does not break Skeleton Walk invisibility.

Name: Burning Barrage
Description: CHANNELED - Clinkz channels and shoots multiple piercing arrows in the target direction that hit all enemy units dealing a percentage of Clinkz' attack damage and applying attack modifiers, and dousing enemies with Tar Bomb slow.

Name: Searing Arrows
Description: Imbues Clinkz's arrows with fire for extra damage.

Name: Skeleton Walk
Description: Clinkz moves invisibly through units until the moment he attacks or uses items. Leaving Skeleton Walk creates Skeleton Archers.

Name: Burning Army
Description: Summons a row of Burning Skeleton Archers in the target location.

Name: Death Pact
Description:
Clinkz consumes the target enemy creep or friendly Skeleton Archer and creates a Skeleton Archer in their place, healing and gaining max health. Does not take Clinkz out of Skeleton Walk.

Only one archer can be summoned from Death Pact at a time.
AbilityDraftNote: Searing Arrows must also be drafted for Burning Army archers to have the extra damage.

Name: Bone and Arrow
Description:
Clinkz summons a Skeleton Archer when he dies. Skeleton Archers are immobile and die within multiple attacks from a hero. Skeleton Archers deal a percentage of Clinkz' damage, and deal less damage to buildings. Attack range is equal to Clinkz' attack range.

Some of Clinkz' other abilities can also summon Skeleton Archers.

Name: Tar Bomb
Description:
Clinkz throws a projectile filled with tar at the target enemy, dealing Magic damage on impact. After impact, the tar spills onto the ground and stays there for %ground_duration% seconds. Any enemy that walks across it gets slowed, and attacks from Clinkz or his Skeleton Archers will deal bonus physical damage.

When the Tar Bomb hits, any Skeleton Archers within attack range will attack the target.

Name: Creep Ability
Description: This slot will be replaced with abilities acquired using Death Pact.

Name: Tar Bomb Multishot
Description: Any attack on enemy covered in tar will send another arrow into a random enemy within Clinkz's attack range.

Name: Arcane Orb
Description: Adds extra pure damage to Outworld Destroyer's attacks, based on his remaining mana pool.

Name: Ominous Discernment
Description: Outworld Destroyer gains an additional %bonus_max_mana_per_int% mana per point of Intelligence.

Name: Astral Imprisonment
Description: Places a target unit into an astral prison. The hidden unit is invulnerable and disabled. When the astral prison implodes, it deals damage to the target and steals a percentage of their max mana.

Name: Essence Aura
Description: Whenever nearby allied Heroes or Outworld Destroyer itself casts a spell, it gains a chance to restore a percentage of its mana pool.  Outworld Destroyer also passively gains a bonus to its base mana pool.  Several skills with no cooldown and toggled spells cannot trigger Essence Aura.

Name: Essence Flux
Description: Passively grants a chance to restore a percentage of your max mana each time you cast an ability.

Name: Sanity's Eclipse
Description: Unleashes a psychic blast that deals damage to enemies based on the difference between your mana and the target's mana. Sanity's Eclipse can hit units trapped by Astral Imprisonment. Deals bonus damage to illusions.

Name: +{s:bonus_mana_as_ms}% of Current Mana as Movement Speed
Disruption
Description: Banishes the targeted unit from the battlefield for a short duration.  Upon returning, two illusions of the banished unit with bonus base damage are created under Shadow Demon's control.

Name: Soul Catcher
Description: Captures the soul of enemy units in an area, causing them to lose a percentage of their current health. Shadow Demon temporarily gains Spell Amplification for each hero's soul captured. When the debuff is removed, the units gain half of the lost health back. Units under the effect of Disruption can still be affected by Soul Catcher.

Name: Shadow Servant
Description: Shadow Demon creates illusions of heroes that die near him.

Name: Shadow Poison
Description: Deals damage in a line, and afflicts enemy units with a poison effect. The poison deals 1/2/4/8/16 times the stack damage based on the number of stacks on the target, up to %max_multiply_stacks% stacks. Additional stacks cause %bonus_stack_damage% damage each.  This deferred damage is dealt when Shadow Poison's duration is expired, or the Release sub-ability is used.
AbilityDraftNote: In Ability Draft, Shadow Poison Release works by toggling auto-cast off, either by right-clicking the ability, or using the alt-hotkey combo.  Auto-cast state will be on if there are any units with Shadow Poison applied.

Name: Shadow Poison Release
Description: Releases the poison to do damage on all affected enemies. Units under the effect of Disruption can still be affected by Shadow Poison.

Name: Demonic Purge
Description:
Purges the target enemy unit, removing positive buffs, and slowing the target for the duration.  The unit slowly regains its speed until the end of the duration, upon which damage is dealt.  Units under the effect of Disruption can still be affected by Demonic Purge.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Demonic Cleanse
Description:
Cleanses the target allied unit, removing negative buffs for the duration. At the end of the duration, the unit is healed. Units under the effect of Disruption can still be affected by Demonic Cleanse.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Disseminate
Description: Whenever the target takes damage, all enemies, including the target itself if it is an enemy, within %radius% range of the target also receive a portion of that damage. Can target enemy and allied units. Effect is paused if the target is hidden by Disruption.

Name: Menace
Description: Shadow Demon's Attacks apply a stacking %stack%% Amplify Damage debuff to the enemy for %duration% seconds.

Name: Summon Wolves
Description: Summons %wolf_count% wolves to aid Lycan in battle. At level 3, wolves gain Permanent Invisibility, and at level 4 wolves gain Cripple that gives 20% chance to cripple the target, causing 8 damage per second and lose 60 attack speed for 4 seconds.

Name: Wolf Bite
Description: Lycan bites an ally, granting them Shapeshift properties. Lycan and the bitten target gain %lifesteal_percent%% Lifesteal and share the healing effect of Lifesteal with each other as long as they are within %lifesteal_range% range of each other.

Name: Howl
Description: Strikes fear into enemies, reducing armor and attack damage of all enemies within %radius% range of Lycan and his wolves. At night, Howl's armor and attack damage reductions are global.

Name: Feral Impulse
Description: Increases the HP regeneration and damage of Lycan and all units under his control.

Name: Shapeshift
Description: Lycan assumes his lupine form, granting him critical strikes and added vision at night. During Shapeshift, Lycan moves at increased speed and cannot be slowed.
AbilityDraftNote: Ranged heroes will lose attack range during Shapeshift, though bonus range abilities can modify that (i.e. Arctic Burn)

Name: Cripple
Description: Gives %maim_chance%% to cripple the target, causing %maim_damage% damage per second and lose %maim_attack_speed% Attack Speed for %maim_duration% seconds.

Name: Invisibility
Description: Permanently invisible when not attacking.

Name: Ferocious Bite
Description: Attacks have a %bash_chance%% chance to deal extra damage and briefly stun their target. Bonus damage is dealt to buildings, but they are not stunned.

Name: Hamstring
Description: The wolf bites down on an enemy's hamstring, rooting them for a short duration. After the bite, the next %damage_boost_stacks% attacks from units controlled by Lycan deal bonus damage.

Name: Hightail
Description: The wolf gains a short burst of energy, gaining phased movement, evasion, hasted movement speed, and attack speed.

Name: Apex Predator
Description: Deal %damage_amp_per_level%% extra damage to neutral creeps per hero level.

Name: Gift Bearer
Description: Lone Druid can re-roll his Neutral Token once per tier.

Name: Bear Necessities
Description: Lone Druid can only use the first %item_slots% items in his inventory. These items' passive bonuses are more powerful. Other item slots do not provide any bonuses. Neutral slot is unaffected.

Name: Summon Spirit Bear
Description:
Summons a powerful Spirit Bear companion that can equip items. Neutral Items are copied from, and share a cooldown with, Lone Druid's own Neutral Items.

If the bear moves %bear_attack_leash_range% distance away from the Lone Druid, it cannot attack. Lone Druid suffers %backlash_damage%% of his max health as backlash damage if the Spirit Bear dies. Spirit Bear has the Return, Demolish and Entangling Claws abilities.

Name: Rabid
Description: Increases the attack and movement speed of Lone Druid and the Spirit Bear.

Name: Spirit Link
Description: Links Lone Druid and the Spirit Bear, increasing their attack speed as well as sharing a percentage of their armor and lifesteal with each other.

Name: Savage Roar
Description: Lone Druid and the Spirit Bear roar fiercely causing nearby enemies to flee towards their base in terror. Their movement speed is increased by %bonus_speed%%.

Name: Savage Roar
Description: Lone Druid and the Spirit Bear roar fiercely causing nearby enemies to flee towards their base in terror. Their movement speed is increased by %bonus_speed%%.

Name: True Form
Description: Lone Druid starts a transformation into a raging bear that has enhanced attack and defensive capabilities.

Name: Druid Form
Description: Return to Druid form.

Name: Battle Cry
Description: Adds attack damage and armor to the Lone Druid as well as any nearby units under his control.

Name: Return
Description: Channels for %channel_tooltip% seconds and then teleports the Spirit Bear back to the Lone Druid.

Name: Entangling Claws
Description: Attacks have a chance to cause roots to burst from the ground, immobilizing the attacked enemy unit, and dealing damage per second.

Name: Entangling Claws
Description: Cause roots to burst from the ground, immobilizing the target enemy unit and causes them to take more damage from attacks. Enemies can still move and attack while entangled.

Name: Defender
Description: Spirit Bear absorbs %damage_share%% of the damage dealt to Lone Druid.

Name: Fetch
Description: Grabs the Target Ally, Enemy or Rune, and uncontrollably drags them towards Lone Druid for the duration. Enemies receive damage every %tick_rate%s. When dragging a unit, they are Rooted.

Name: Demolish
Description: Increases the power of the Spirit Bear, causing it to deal more damage to buildings and have additional magic resistance.

Name: Thunder Clap
Description: Slams the ground, dealing damage and slowing the movement speed and attack rate of nearby enemy units.

Name: Drunken Haze
Description: Drenches a target in alcohol, causing their movement speed to be reduced, and causing their attacks to have a chance to miss.

Name: Cinder Brew
Description: Drenches himself and an area in alcohol, causing enemy units to move slower and ignite once they take any Magic or Pure damage. Duration is increased by %extra_duration% seconds when enemies are ignited. While Brewmaster is Brewed Up, His Drunken Brawler Stances are stronger. Dealing or receiving magic damage extends Brewmaster's Brewed Up duration.

Name: Drunken Brawler
Description:
Brewmaster can switch stances based on the elements he controls, gaining passive bonuses that improve against enemies when Brewed Up.
<font color="#9acd32">Earth Brawler</font> - Grants %armor% armor and %magic_resist%% Magic Resistance. Bonuses are %active_multiplier%x when Brewed Up.
<font color="#87ceeb">Storm Brawler</font> - Grants %dodge_chance%% evasion and %bonus_move_speed%% Bonus Move Speed. Bonuses are %active_multiplier%x when Brewed Up.
<font color="#FF0000">Fire Brawler</font> - Grants %crit_chance%% chance to critical strike for %crit_multiplier%% of your attack damage and %attack_speed% Attack Speed. Crit Chance and Attack Speed is %active_multiplier%x when Brewed Up.
 <font color="#662375">Void Brawler</font> - Grants %bonus_status_resist%% bonus Status Resistance to Brewmaster and applies a %movespeed%% Slow for %slow_duration%s on attack. Slow and Status Resistance are %active_multiplier%x when affected by Cinder Brew.

Name: Belligerent
Description: Brewmaster gains %damage_pct%% bonus attack damage for %damage_duration_split%s when he comes out of Primal Split and for %damage_duration_respawn%s when he respawns.

Name: Primal Split
Description: Splits Brewmaster into elements, forming 4 specialized warriors, adept at survival, each with their own abilities. If any of them survive until the end of their summoned timer, the Brewmaster is reborn.

Name: Primal Split Cancel
Description: Cancel the Primal Split.

Name: Primal Companion
Description:
Creates a Brewling based on Brewmaster's current Drunken Brawler Stance.

A new Brewling cannot be resummoned for %cooldown_on_take_damage%s if the current one takes damage from enemy Heroes or hero-controlled units. If the Brewling dies, the ability goes on cooldown for %cooldown_on_death% seconds.

Only one Brewling can exist at a time. If Brewmaster uses Primal Split, the existing Brewling disappears.

Name: Hurl Boulder
Description: Throws a boulder at a unit, doing damage and stunning it.

Name: Astral Pulse
Description: Disarms and slows movement speed of nearby enemies.

Name: Debuff Immunity
Description: Immune to debuffs. Magic resistance increased by %magic_resist%%.

Name: Demolish
Description: Deals bonus damage to buildings.

Name: Dispel Magic
Description:
Damages summoned units in an area and dispels most buffs or debuffs.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Cyclone
Description: Encloses a unit in a tornado, removing it from the battlefield.

Name: Wind Walk
Description: Provides temporary invisibility.  Bonus movement speed and attack damage when invisible.

Name: Permanent Immolation
Description: Burns nearby enemy units.

Name: Permanent Phase
Description: Provides the Brewling with phased movement and bonus Status Resistance.

Name: Astral Pull
Description: Pulls the target and the Void Brewling in the target direction. Enemies are damaged upon arrival.

Name: Cinder Brew applies Fear when ignited
Description: Lasts 1.5 seconds.

Name: +{s:bonus_active_multiplier}x Brewed Up multiplier for Drunken Brawler
Spirit Lance
Description: Sends a magical spirit lance to a target enemy unit that damages and slows, while summoning an illusory phantom to attack the unit.

Name: Doppelganger
Description:
Phantom Lancer briefly vanishes from the battlefield. After %delay% second, Phantom Lancer and any of his nearby illusions reappear at a random position within the targeted location, along with two additional doppelgangers. Extends duration of all illusions. The two added doppelgangers have different properties: one takes normal damage and deals none, while the other takes %illusion_2_damage_in_pct%% bonus damage and deals %illusion_2_damage_out_pct%% less damage.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Juxtapose
Description: Phantom Lancer has a chance to fracture his presence on an attack, creating an illusion of himself. Illusions also have a chance to fracture further. Illusions created from Phantom Lancer last for %illusion_duration% seconds, while illusions created from other illusions last %illusion_from_illusion_duration% seconds.

Name: Phantom Rush
Description: When targeting an enemy for an attack, Phantom Lancer quickly charges into range, gaining a temporary agility boost. Phantom Lancer's illusions also have this ability.

Name: Illusory Armaments
Description: Items, abilities, and auras that grant bonus damage instead grant base damage.

Name: Nature's Guise
Description: Provides Treant with Tree Walking whenever he hasn't taken damage for %cooldown_time% seconds. While nearby trees or affected by Nature's Grasp, Treant gains bonus movement speed.

Name: Nature's Grasp
Description: Creates vines towards the target location. Vines slow down and deal damage to enemies that walk through. Vines deal 50% more damage if they touch a tree. Does half damage to creeps.

Name: Leech Seed
Description: Treant plants a life-sapping seed in an enemy unit, draining its health, while simultaneously slowing it. The seed heals friendly units around it. Healing to creeps is reduced by %creep_heal_reduction_pct%%.

Name: Living Armor
Description: Infuses the target hero or structure with a protective coating which heals the target and provides bonus armor.

Name: Overgrowth
Description: Summons an overgrowth of vines and branches around Treant that deal damage to afflicted enemies and prevent them from moving, blinking, going invisible, or attacking.

Name: Eyes In The Forest
Description: Treant Protector enchants a tree, which grants him unobstructed vision in that location. If Overgrowth is cast, units within a radius of an enchanted tree will be entangled and damaged. Passively causes all trees to respawn much faster.

Name: Dumb Luck
Description: Ogre Magi's max Intelligence is 0. He receives mana and mana regeneration from Strength.

Name: Fireblast
Description: Blasts an enemy unit with a wave of fire, dealing damage and stunning the target.
AbilityDraftNote: Scepter: Access Unrefined Fireblast by toggling auto-cast on Fireblast.

Name: Fire Shield
Description: Creates a shield around the target ally, absorbing a percentage of the damage of next %attacks% attacks from enemy heroes. When damage is absorbed, a fireball is launched at the attacker. Can be cast on towers.

Name: Unrefined Fireblast
Description: Blasts an enemy unit with a wave of fire, dealing %base_damage% + %str_multiplier%x Ogre's Strength in damage and stunning the target. Its mana cost is %scepter_mana%% of Ogre Magi's current mana.

Name: Ignite
Description: Drenches the target and another random unit in volatile chemicals, causing it to burst into flames. The target is in immense pain, taking damage and moving more slowly.

Name: Bloodlust
Description: Incites a frenzy in a friendly unit, increasing its movement speed and attack speed. Gives bonus attacks speed if cast on Ogre himself. Can be cast on towers.

Name: Multicast
Description: Enables Ogre Magi to cast his abilities and items multiple times with each use.

Name: Ice Armor
Description: The Ogre Frostmage summons an invisible layer of icy air that surrounds the target friendly unit, increasing its armor and temporarily slowing any enemies that dare attack it.

Name: -{s:bonus_AbilityCooldown}s Fireblast Cooldown
Description: Also reduces cooldown of Unrefined Fireblast

Name: +{s:bonus_mana_per_str}/{s:bonus_mana_regen_per_str} Dumb Luck Mana/Mana Regen Per Strength
Chaos Bolt
Description: Throws a mysterious bolt of energy at the target unit. It stuns for a random duration and deals random damage.

Name: Reality Rift
Description: Teleports Chaos Knight, any illusions he has, and the target unit to a point along the line between him and the target. Reduces armor of the enemy unit for %duration% seconds.

Name: Chaos Strike
Description: Chaos Knight and his illusions' attacks have a chance to deal a critical strike of varying strength with bonus lifesteal. Deals %creep_multiplier%x damage to creeps, but lifesteal from creeps is reduced by %creep_lifesteal_reduction_pct%%.

Name: Phantasm
Description:
Summons several phantasmal copies of the Chaos Knight from alternate dimensions. The phantasms are illusions that deal %outgoing_damage_tooltip%% damage, but take %incoming_damage_tooltip%% damage.
DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Phantasmagoria
Description: All Chaos Knight Illusions are Strong Illusions and take less damage when near him.

Name: Reins of Chaos
Description: Whenever illusions of Chaos Knight are created, there is a %bonus_illusion_chance%% chance that an additional %bonus_illusion_count% extra illusion will spawn.

Name: Fan of Knives
Description: Phantom Assassin releases sharp blades around her, dealing a percentage of each victim's max health on impact and applying Break.

Name: Stifling Dagger
Description: Throws a dagger slowing the enemy unit's movement speed, dealing %base_damage%+%attack_factor_tooltip%% of Phantom Assassin's attack damage as physical damage and applying attack effects from items and abilities.

Name: Phantom Strike
Description: Teleports to a unit, friendly or enemy, and grants bonus attack speed while attacking if it's an enemy unit.

Name: Immaterial
Description:
Phantom Assassin focuses inward, increasing her ability to evade enemy attacks. Evasion improves with Phantom Assassin's levels. 

Stacks diminishingly with other sources of Evasion.

Name: Blur
Description: Phantom Assassin blurs her body, disjointing incoming projectiles, increasing her movement speed, causing her to be impossible to see until she attacks or comes near enemy heroes, towers, or outposts.
AbilityDraftNote: With Scepter, only non-ultimate spells will refresh.

Name: Coup de Grace
Description: Phantom Assassin refines her combat abilities, acquiring a chance of gaining Deadly Focus with each attack. When attacking with Deadly Focus, Phantom Assassin will consume the buff and guarantee a critical hit. Stifling Dagger has a bonus chance to cause Deadly Focus.

Name: Triple Strike Stifling Dagger
Description: Launches two extra Stifling Daggers towards random visible enemies within the cast range.

Name: Rocket Barrage
Description: Launches a salvo of rockets at nearby enemy units in a radius around the Gyrocopter. Lasts %barrage_duration% seconds.

Name: Homing Missile
Description: Fires a homing missile to seek the targeted enemy unit. The missile gains speed over time, dealing damage and stunning when it impacts the target. Enemy units can destroy the missile before it reaches its target.

Name: Flak Cannon
Description: Gyrocopter's attacks hit all enemy units in an area around it for a limited number of attacks.  Only the main target of attacks will receive attack bonuses such as Critical Strike.  Lasts %abilityduration% seconds or until the attacks are used.

Name: Call Down
Description: Call down %total_strikes% aerial missile strikes that slow and damage enemy units in a target area. Each strike is %strike_separation% distance from the previous one.

Name: Chop Shop
Description: Gyrocopter can disassemble most items.

Name: Telekinesis
Description: Rubick uses his telekinetic powers to lift the enemy into the air briefly and then hurls them back at the ground. The unit lands on the ground with such force that it stuns nearby enemies.

Name: Telekinesis Land
Description: Chooses the location the target will land when Telekinesis finishes.

Name: Telekinesis Land
Description: Chooses the location you will land when Telekinesis finishes.

Name: Fade Bolt
Description: Rubick creates a powerful stream of arcane energy that travels between enemy units, dealing damage and reducing their attack damage. Each jump deals less damage.

Name: Null Field
Description: Rubick's mastery of the arcane creates an aura that nullifies nearby enemy senses or increases his own. Can be toggled offensively or defensively to reduce enemy magic resistance or increase allied magic resistance.

Name: Arcane Supremacy
Description: Rubick's mastery of the arcane allows him to have a larger cast range and increased potency.

Name: Might and Magus
Description: Each %one_tooltip%% Spell Amplification also increases Rubick's attack damage by %bonus_damage_pct_tooltip%% and Magic Resistance by %magic_resist_pct_tooltip%%.

Name: Spell Steal
Description: Rubick studies the trace magical essence of one enemy hero, learning the secrets of the last spell the hero cast. Rubick can use this spell as his own for several minutes or until he dies, and stolen spells last longer on enemies.

Name: Stolen Spell
Description: Spells acquired with Spell Steal will replace this slot.

Name: Stolen Spell
Description: Spells acquired with Spell Steal will replace this slot.

Name: Lucent Beam
Description: Calls a beam of lunar energy down upon an enemy, damaging and briefly stunning them.

Name: Lunar Orbit
Description: Creates %rotating_glaives% glaives that rotate %rotating_glaives_movement_radius% radius around Luna. Any enemy unit that collides with a glaive will take a percentage of Luna's Attack Damage.

Name: Moon Glaives
Description: Empowers Luna's glaives, causing her attacks to bounce between enemy units. Deals less damage with each bounce.
AbilityDraftNote: Moon Glaives work on all melee heroes.

Name: Lunar Blessing
Description: Grants %bonus_damage_per_level% attack damage per level to Luna and nearby allied heroes, with Luna receiving double the attack damage bonuses. At night, Lunar Blessing is global, and Luna is blessed with %bonus_night_vision_self% bonus night vision + %bonus_night_vision_per_level% per level.

Name: Lunar Blessing
Description: Dispels negative buffs and grants you bonus attack speed. Has an increased effect during the night.

Name: Eclipse
Description: Showers random nearby enemies with strikes from Luna's current level of Lucent Beam. These beams do not stun their targets, and there is a maximum number of times that a single target can be struck. Also turns day into night for a short time.
AbilityDraftNote: Must draft Lucent Beam as well to work.

Name: Lucent Beam Hits An Additional Target
Description: Random target within {s:bonus_lucent_beam_bounce_range} range of the primary target.

Name: {s:bonus_glaives_fired} Moon Glaives fired on Lucent Beam
Description: Does not fire Glaives on Beams from Eclipse

Name: Tether
Description: Tethers Io to an allied unit, granting bonus movement speed to both. When Io restores health or mana, the tethered unit gains a portion of that amount. The tether breaks when the allied unit moves too far away, or Io cancels the tether. Tether slows and damages enemies touching it.

Name: Spirits
Description: Summon five particle spirits that dance in a circle around Io. If a particle collides with an enemy hero, it explodes, damaging all enemy units in an area around it.  Creeps take minor damage from touching a particle spirit, but do not cause them to explode.  When its duration ends, any remaining Spirits explode.

Name: Overcharge
Description: Io gains health regeneration based on max health.  If Io is Tethered to an ally, that unit also gains any bonuses granted by Overcharge.

Name: Relocate
Description: Teleports Io and a tethered ally to any location. After the spell expires, Io and the tethered ally will return to their original location. Double-click to teleport to your team's base fountain.

Name: Break Tether
Description: Break the link to the tethered unit.

Name: Spirits In
Description: Sends the spirits closer to you. Can be toggled on and off.

Name: Spirits Out
Description: Sends the spirits farther away from you. Can be toggled on and off.

Name: Sight Seer
Description: Io's Team takes %bonus_channel_speed%s less to take watchers, and their watchers have %bonus_vision% bonus vision.

Name: Attack Tethered Ally's Target ({s:bonus_tether_attack_damage_pct}% damage)
Description: While tethered to a friendly Hero, each time that Hero attacks, Io will attack the same target automatically.

Name: Thunder Strike
Description: Repeatedly strikes the targeted unit with lightning.  Each strike damages nearby enemy units in a small radius and slows enemy movement and attack speed by %slow_amount%% for %slow_duration% seconds.  Provides vision of its target.

Name: Glimpse
Description: Teleports the target hero back to where it was %backtrack_time% seconds ago.  Instantly kills illusions. Deals damage equal to a percentage of the distance glimpsed, that cannot go over a damage maximum.

Name: Kinetic Field
Description: After a short formation time, creates a circular barrier of kinetic energy that enemies can't pass.

Name: Kinetic Fence
Description: After a short formation time, creates a wall out of kinetic energy that enemies cannot pass.

Name: Static Storm
Description: Creates a damaging static storm that also silences all enemy units in the area for the duration.  The damage starts off weak, but increases in power over the duration.

Name: Electromagnetic Repulsion
Description: Whenever Disruptor takes more than %damage_threshold% damage from any source within %effect_radius% radius, all nearby enemies within are pushed back up to a %effect_radius% unit distance.

Name: +{s:bonus_strike_damage_bonus} Thunder Strike Damage per Strike
Description: Every strike increases the damage of subsequent strikes until the debuff expires

Name: Decay
Description: Undying steals strength from all enemy heroes in an area, dealing base damage as he claims the enemy's strength for himself. Deals %creep_damage_multiplier%x damage to creeps.

Name: Soul Rip
Description: Undying rips health away from all nearby units and uses it to heal an ally, or damage an enemy. Soul Rip can also be used to heal Tombstone.

Name: Tombstone
Description: Summons a tombstone at the target point.  Zombies will frequently spawn next to every enemy unit in the area around the Tombstone, and attack them.  Zombies have the Deathlust ability, which causes their attacks to slow the target, and if the target reaches below a certain amount of health, increases the attack and movement speed of the zombie.

Name: Deathlust
Description: Slows enemy units on attack.  If the attacked unit's health goes below the threshold, the zombie receives enhanced movement and attack speed.

Name: Flesh Golem
Description: Undying transforms into a horrifying flesh golem. Gains a percentage increase to strength and imbues attacks with a slow and damage amplification.

Name: Grab Ally
Description: Load an ally into the nearest available tombstone.

Name: Grab Ally
Description: Load an ally into this tombstone.

Name: Ceaseless Dirge
Description: When Undying dies he will instantly respawn in the fountain. Begins the game on cooldown. Cannot be refreshed.

Name: Refraction
Description: Templar Assassin becomes highly elusive, gaining a small barrier and bonus to her damage.  The damage and avoidance effects are separate, and have a limited number of instances. If a barrier is consumed, a new one is created as long as there are charges left. If an instance of damage would deal more damage than the remaining barrier, all of the damage is absorbed.

Name: Meld
Description: Templar Assassin conceals herself, becoming invisible as long as she remains still.  If Meld's invisibility is broken by attacking an enemy, Lanaya will deal bonus damage to the enemy and reduce their armor for %abilityduration% seconds.

Name: Psi Blades
Description: Templar Assassin's psi blades slice through the attacked unit, splitting and damaging enemy units directly behind it, while gaining bonus attack range. For each unit it damages, the spill damage is reduced by a percentage.

Name: Psionic Trap
Description: Templar Assassin places mystical traps that invisibly monitor enemy movement. When sprung at her command, they deal a small amount of damage and exert a slowing influence of %movement_speed_min%% in the area. Traps charge up to slow %movement_speed_max%% after %trap_max_charge_duration% seconds. Deals bonus damage when fully charged.

Name: Third Eye
Description: Templar Assassin and her teammates can see Roshan's respawn timer.

Name: Trap
Description:
Springs the trap nearest to Templar Assassin, slowing nearby enemies.

If the ability is in alt-cast state, springs the trap that is closest to the mouse cursor.

Name: Psionic Projection
Description: CHANNELED - Allows Templar Assassin to teleport to any Psionic Trap after channeling for %abilitychanneltime% seconds, detonating it upon arrival as if it was fully charged and instantly dealing %extra_damage% bonus damage. Channeling Psionic Projection does not break Meld.

Name: Trap
Description: Springs the trap, slowing nearby enemies.

Name: Refraction Dispels
Description: Applies a basic dispel to Templar Assassin.

Name: +{s:value} Psi Blades Attack and Spill Range
Refraction Can Be Cast While Disabled
Mirror Image
Description:
Creates multiple images of Naga Siren under her control.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Ensnare
Description: Interrupts the target and traps them in place, preventing movement or blinking. Can target invulnerable and sleeping units.

Name: Rip Tide
Description: Naga Siren and her illusions deal bonus damage to enemies and reduce their armor for %duration% seconds every %hits% attacks.

Name: Deluge
Description: Naga Siren and all of her images hit nearby units with a damaging wave of water that reduces enemy status resistance and caps their max movement speed.

Name: Eelskin
Description: Naga Siren gets %evasion_per_naga%% evasion per other Naga Siren within %radius% radius.

Name: Critical Strike
Description: Attacks inflict critical damage.

Name: Song of the Siren
Description: All enemies in range of the Naga Siren are put into a magical stasis where they cannot act or be attacked. Allies in range recover a percentage of their health per second. Using Song of the Siren again will end the duration early.

Name: Song of the Siren End
Description: Release enemy units from your song so they can be targeted again.

Name: Reel In
Description: CHANNELED - Naga Siren channels for up to %AbilityChannelTime% seconds, pulling all units affected by Naga's Ensnare in a %radius% range towards her at a speed of %pull_strength%. Channeling ends when the Ensnared unit is %min_pull_distance% distance away.

Name: Impale
Description: Rock spikes burst from the earth along a straight path. Enemy units take damage, then are hurled into the air and stunned.

Name: Mana Burn
Description: Destroys the target hero's mana equal to a multiplier of its Intelligence, and deals damage equal to the mana burned.

Name: Mind Flare
Description: Deals damages to the enemy equal to a percentage of its Max Mana. Additionally deals damage equal to a percentage of damage the target received from Nyx Assassin in the past %damage_echo_duration%s. Instantly kills non-ancient creeps.

Name: Spiked Carapace
Description:
When activated while above ground, Spiked Carapace reflects and negates damage dealt to Nyx Assassin (max once from each source), as well as stunning the source of the damage. Activating Spiked Carapace will not break Vendetta invisibility.

While Burrowed, Spiked Carapace instantly stuns nearby enemies when cast.

Name: Vendetta
Description: Allows Nyx Assassin to become invisible and gain a speed bonus.  If Nyx Assassin attacks to break the invisibility, massive bonus damage is dealt with the attack. Nyx Assassin has %attack_range_bonus% additional attack range and a %attack_animation_bonus%% faster attack animation for this attack.

Name: Burrow
Description: Nyx Assassin buries himself beneath the battlefield over a short duration. Once burrowed, Spiked Carapace instantly stuns nearby enemies when cast, the range of Mind Flare and Impale is increased, and Impale's cooldown is decreased. While burrowed, Nyx Assassin is stationary, unable to attack, and invisible. Nyx gains damage reduction from all damage sources.

Name: Unburrow
Description: Emerge from the burrow.

Name: Nyxth Sense
Description: Nyx Assassin can detect heroes within %radius% units of himself.

Name: Mana Burn
Description: Nyx Assassin's ability damage burns enemies' mana.

Name: Vendetta Applies Break
Description: Lasts for {s:bonus_break_duration} seconds.

Name: Illuminate
Description: CHANNELED - Channels light energy, building power the longer it's channeled.  Once released, a wave is sent forth that deals damage and gives vision in its path.  The longer it is channeled, the more damage is dealt.

Name: Mana Leak
Description: Weakens an enemy's magical essence, causing them to lose mana as they move.  If the enemy loses all of its mana, it will be stunned.

Name: Solar Bind
Description: Weakens an enemy's magical resistance, and applies a slow that increases in strength the more the target moves.

Name: Will-O-Wisp
Description: Summons Ignis Fatuus at the targeted area. Alternates on and off, drawing enemies closer with its mesmerising flicker.

Name: Chakra Magic
Description: Restores mana to the target unit and reduces cooldowns of all basic abilities currently on cooldown by a fixed amount. Is %self_bonus%% more effective when used on himself.

Name: Spirit Form
Description: Ezalor temporarily turns his body luminescent, gaining bonus movement speed, cast range, and allows Illuminate to be channeled by a separate spirit and heal allies.

Name: Recall
Description:
After a short delay, teleports the targeted friendly hero to your location. If the targeted friendly hero takes player based damage during this time, the ability is interrupted. When cast, the teleport target's movement speed is increased. Upon teleporting, Chakra Magic and the increased movement speed buff are applied to both Keeper of the Light and the teleport target.

If alt-cast, teleports Keeper of the Light to the target Ally instead.

Ability Level increases with levels of Spirit Form.

Name: Blinding Light
Description: A blinding light flashes over the targeted area, knocking back and blinding the units in the area, causing them to miss some attacks. Knockback is %knockback_distance% range over %knockback_duration% seconds.

Name: Release Illuminate
Description: Release the channel early.

Name: Mana Magnifier
Description: Allies within %aura_radius% range of Keeper of the Light have %bonus_mana_pct%% more mana. Lingers for 5 seconds.

Name: Grave Chill
Description: Visage drains the movement and attack speed of the targeted unit, gaining it for itself and nearby familiars.

Name: Soul Assumption
Description: Visage gathers charges of soul essence each time nearby heroes take more than %damage_limit% damage. When the essence is released, it deals base damage as well as damage for each gathered soul charge.

Name: Gravekeeper's Cloak
Description: Visage generates a layered barrier that protects him from damage.  If he receives damage from a player, one layer is removed, and takes time to recover.

Name: Summon Familiars
Description: Conjures %familiar_count% blind Familiars to fight for Visage.  Familiars possess the Stone Form ability, that allows them to turn into stone, stunning enemies upon landing.  While in Stone Form, Familiars are invulnerable, and rapidly regenerate their health.  Familiars grant high bounty when killed.

Name: Silent as the Grave
Description: Turns Visage and familiars invisible, granting Visage bonus movement speed and upgrading its movement type to flying. When Visage or its familiars leave invisibility they deal more damage for a short duration. Lasts %invis_duration% seconds. Invisibility ends when attacking or casting.

Name: Stone Form
Description:
Orders the Familiar closest to Visage to cast Stone Form in its current location, turning into stone and smashing into the ground, stunning and damaging all targets in the area. The Familiar becomes invulnerable, and will regain its health very rapidly. After %stone_duration% seconds, the Familiar will automatically leave Stone Form.

Can be alt-cast to order the closest Familiar to the target location to move there and cast Stone Form.

Name: Stone Form
Description:
After a short delay, the Familiar turns into stone and smashes into the ground, stunning and damaging all targets in the area. The Familiar becomes invulnerable, and will regain its health very rapidly. After %stone_duration% seconds, the Familiar will automatically leave Stone Form.

Can be alt-cast to order the Familiar to move to the target location and cast Stone Form.

Name: Lurker
Description:
Visage's ability cooldown durations are accelerated as long as he's not taking damage.

Grants a stack every %stack_gain_time%s that Visage does not take damage. Each stack grants %cooldown_speed_per_stack%% cooldown acceleration with a max of %max_stacks% stacks. Stacks fade after %linger_duration%s upon taking any damage.

Name: +{s:bonus_armor_reduction_per_hit} Armor Corruption to Visage and Familiars
Description: This effect can stack among multiple sources and lasts {s:bonus_armor_reduction_duration}s.

Name: Soul Assumption Hits {s:value} Targets
Description: A second Soul Assumption is launched towards a random enemy unit within the cast range, prioritizing Heroes.

Name: Dig
Description:
Digs into the ground for a short duration, dispelling Meepo and causing him to become invulnerable and untargetable for %duration%s. Restores %hp_restore%% of his max health over that duration.

DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel

Name: Earthbind
Description: Tosses a net at the target point, rooting down all enemy units in an area around it.

Name: Poof
Description:
Drawing mystical energies from the earth, a Meepo can teleport to another Meepo or itself after channeling for %cast_duration% seconds, damaging the enemy in both the departure and arrival locations.

If the ability is in alt-cast state, all Meepos will also cast Poof to the target. When cast on the ground, all Meepos except the selected one will Poof to the closest location.
AbilityDraftNote: In AD, can poof to any friendly unit within 2000 range.

Name: Ransack
Description: Steals health from the enemy with each strike and heals all other Meepos for that amount.

Name: Divided We Stand
Description: Meepo summons an imperfect, semi-autonomous duplicate of himself, which can gain gold and experience as he does and shares his experience, attributes and abilities. However, the clones cannot wield any items but the boots that Meepo himself wears.  If any of the clones die, they all die. Divided We Stand grants all Meepos bonus Magic Resistance.

Name: MegaMeepo
Description:
Primary Meepo mounts all other Meepos in a %radius% radius around him on top of his shoulders. While in this form, he gains %stats_pct%% of the other Meepo stats and can Fling them at enemies, dealing damage and slowing them.

 When cast, Earthbind generates additional nets and Poof deals bonus damage based on the amount of Meepos riding on top.

Name: MegaMeepo Fling
Description: In MegaMeepo form, Meepo flings the topmost meepo towards a target within a %AbilityCastRange% range, dealing damage and slowing their movement speed.

Name: Pack Rat
Description: All Meepos can use the item in the neutral item slot.

Name: Sticky Fingers
Description: Has an extra choice of neutral item to select from.

Name: Earthbind grants True Strike on Targets
Horn Toss
Description: Magnus tosses any enemies in front of him, launching them to his rear. Enemies take damage, spend %air_duration% seconds in the air, and are stunned while in the air and an additional amount of time after landing.

Name: Shockwave
Description: Magnus sends out a wave of force, damaging enemy units in a line, pulling them towards him, and slowing them for a brief period.

Name: Empower
Description: Gives an allied unit bonus damage and cleave on attack. Magnus receives %self_multiplier%% larger bonus.

Name: Skewer
Description: Magnus rushes forward, goring enemy units on his massive tusk. Heroes hit on the way will be dragged to the destination, then damaged and affected by slowed movement and attack speed. Deals additional damage when skewering enemies into trees or cliffs.

Name: Reverse Polarity
Description: Magnus changes properties of matter, pulling all nearby enemies in front of him and stunning them with a damaging slam.

Name: Solid Core
Description: Magnus has slow resistance and suffers %knockback_reduction%% less knockback from enemy's abilities and items.

Name: Strength of Joelrak
Description: Every time an enemy hero is damaged by an ability, Magnus gains a stacking buff, that provides %strength_per_stack% Strength per stack.

Name: +{s:bonus_stats_per_stack} All Stats per hero hit with Reverse Polarity
Description: Bonus Stats last for {s:bonus_stat_buff_duration}s

Name: Hoof Stomp
Description: After a brief windup, Centaur Warrunner slams the ground, stunning and damaging nearby enemy units. During the delay, he is disarmed but can move.

Name: Double Edge
Description: Centaur strikes a mighty blow at melee range, damaging both himself and a small area around the target. Deals extra damage based on your strength. Centaur cannot die from Double Edge.

Name: Retaliate
Description: Centaur counters all attacks, dealing damage back to the attacker. Returns a fixed amount plus a percentage of your strength. Deals half damage to towers.

Name: Stampede
Description: Centaur leads all allies into a vicious charge causing them to move through units at max speed and slow any enemy units they trample. Trampled enemies take damage based on Centaur Warrunner's strength. Each enemy can be trampled once.

Name: Work Horse
Description: Centaur hitches a cart behind him. While active, Centaur gains the benefit of Stampede for the current level of Stampede, and can cast Hitch a Ride on a target ally.

Name: Horsepower
Description: Centaur Warrunner gains Movement Speed based on his Strength.

Name: Hitch A Ride
Description: Centaur tosses an ally into a cart hitched behind him. While in the cart, the ally is invulnerable and can still cast and attack normally, but cannot move independently or be targeted by opponents. Increases the attack range of melee heroes by %melee_attack_range%.

Name: Rawhide
Description: Permanently gain %health_per_upgrade% max health every %upgrade_rate%s.

Name: Gains Retaliate Aura
Description: Allied heroes within 1200 range of Centaur gain the Return Damage aspect of Retaliate.

Name: Fish Bait
Description: Reduce movement speed of an enemy by %movement_speed%% for %slow_duration% seconds and provide true sight vision over them. If Slark pounces on the enemy during that time, he will be rewarded with %attack_speed% Attack Speed for the duration of the Leash.

Name: Depth Shroud
Description: Creates a cloud at the target location. All allies inside the radius are hidden and affected by Shadow Dance.

Name: Dark Pact
Description:
After a short delay, Slark sacrifices some of his life blood, purging most negative debuffs and dealing damage to enemy units around him and to himself.  Slark only takes %self_damage_pct%% of the damage.

DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel

Name: Pounce
Description: Slark leaps forward, leashing the first hero he connects.  That unit can only move a limited distance away from Slark's landing position.

Name: Essence Shift
Description: Slark steals the life essence of enemy heroes with his attacks, draining each of their attributes and converting them to bonus Agility. If Slark kills an affected enemy hero, he permanently steals %stat_loss% Agility.

Name: Barracuda
Description: When not visible to the enemy team, Slark gains bonus movement speed and health regeneration.

Name: Shadow Dance
Description: When used, Slark hides himself in a cloud of shadows, becoming immune to detection. Attacking, casting spells, and using items will not reveal Slark.

Name: +{s:bonus_agi_gain} Agility gain/stolen per Essence Shift Stack
Flamethrower
Description: Releases a flame in the direction Timbersaw is facing. Applies a debuff that deals damage per second and slows enemy movement speed. Affects buildings for reduced damage.

Name: Whirling Death
Description: Timbersaw whirls extremely sharp edges, damaging enemies and destroying trees around him in an area. If an enemy hero is affected, it loses some of its primary attribute for a short duration. Whirling Death will deal bonus damage per tree destroyed.

Name: Timber Chain
Description: Timbersaw fires a chain that embeds itself in the first tree it hits, pulling him towards it.  Any enemy in the path takes damage.

Name: Reactive Armor
Description: Each time Timbersaw is attacked, he gains increased health regen and armor. Hero attacks are counted as %stacks_per_hero_attack%x the amount.

Name: Chakram
Description: Fires Timbersaw's main saw blade at the target location where it will spin in place, dealing damage in an area around it.  Enemies caught in the saw blade will move more slowly for every %slow_health_percentage%% of health missing. The blade deals damage and cuts down trees in its path when fired and retracted.  While active the ability costs mana, and Timbersaw loses the ability to attack.

Name: Second Chakram
Description: Launches a second independent Chakram. Chakram and Second Chakram damage reduced by %damage_penalty_tooltip%%.

Name: Return Chakram
Description: Returns the Chakram to Timbersaw.

Name: Return Second Chakram
Description: Returns the Chakram to Timbersaw.

Name: Twisted Chakram
Description: Launches a second independent Chakram that follows a curved path and returns to Timbersaw, damaging and slowing enemies it passes through. Enemies caught in the saw blade will move more slowly for every %slow_health_percentage%% of health missing.

Name: Exposure Therapy
Description: Whenever Timbersaw destroys a tree, he gains %mana_restore% mana.

Name: +{s:bonus_stack_limit} Max / +{s:bonus_stacks_per_hero_attack} Hero Attack Reactive Armor Stacks
Cold Blooded
Description: When Medusa is targeted with a spell, a single-target Mystic Snake is sent back towards the enemy.

Name: Split Shot
Description:
Medusa magically splits her shot into several arrows. These arrows deal a lower percent of her normal damage.

The extra targets will not receive other attack effects (such as critical strike).

Name: Mystic Snake
Description: A mystic snake made of energy jumps from target to target dealing damage. Damage and speed increases with each jump. After it reaches its last target, it returns to Medusa to replenish her with mana. The snake returns a percentage of the targets' total mana.
AbilityDraftNote:
Shard: Cold Blooded is hidden in the ability panel when Shard is aquired, but a buff icon will appear.

Stone Gaze must be drafted for Aghanim's Scepter upgrade to work.

Name: Mana Shield
Description: Creates a shield that absorbs %absorption_pct%% of incoming damage in exchange for Medusa's mana that increases with each level of Medusa. Illusions absorb %illusion_percentage%% less damage per point of mana.
AbilityDraftNote: Medusa begins the game with a level one Mana Shield if not drafted. Mana Shield's max level is 4 when drafted by other heroes.

Name: Stone Gaze
